1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Beijing Film Studio

2
00:00:13,192 --> 00:00:20,966
Counterattack

3
00:02:17,340 --> 00:02:18,860
Ready!

4
00:02:20,220 --> 00:02:22,385
Move aside!

5
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:27,927
Ready...

6
00:02:28,733 --> 00:02:30,055
Fire!

7
00:02:36,336 --> 00:02:37,493
Fire!

8
00:02:46,171 --> 00:02:47,671
Fire!

9
00:02:55,477 --> 00:02:57,040
Comrade Derong Ding!

10
00:02:57,717 --> 00:02:59,259
Old Ding!

11
00:03:00,230 --> 00:03:01,294
Oh, Comrade Old Geng!

12
00:03:01,381 --> 00:03:02,081
Yes

13
00:03:02,249 --> 00:03:03,000
Everything looks good.

14
00:03:03,259 --> 00:03:04,528
The dam body is stable.

15
00:03:05,555 --> 00:03:12,910
Today’s blast test proves that the “three-in-one combination's” plan—opening the bottom outlet and tunnel—is fully feasible.

16
00:03:12,910 --> 00:03:16,180
This way, the silt in the reservoir can be flushed out.

17
00:03:16,180 --> 00:03:20,340
Ha ha! This is the result of open-door education, learning from the working class!

18
00:03:20,340 --> 00:03:24,060
Ha ha, that’s right.

19
00:03:45,332 --> 00:03:48,260
Hey, Dachuang, hurry!

20
00:03:48,260 --> 00:03:50,040
Auntie Tian brought mung bean sweet soup!

21
00:03:50,040 --> 00:03:52,060
Then let everyone take a break.

22
00:03:52,060 --> 00:03:54,570
Auntie Tian!

23
00:03:54,570 --> 00:03:58,460
Hey, Dachuang! Students, come over!

24
00:03:58,460 --> 00:04:02,850
It’s hot today. Have some mung bean soup and fresh cucumbers!

25
00:04:02,850 --> 00:04:09,960
Students: Auntie!

26
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:16,208
Thank you auntie!

27
00:04:16,208 --> 00:04:18,430
Pass it out.

28
00:04:18,430 --> 00:04:22,330
Wow, Shen Niu, this soup is exactly what I need!

29
00:04:22,330 --> 00:04:26,100
Auntie, another bowl, please!

30
00:04:26,100 --> 00:04:28,540
Drink up, kids. Today, Auntie’s treating everyone!

31
00:04:30,420 --> 00:04:33,060
Sister Xiao Hong, there are fresh cucumbers too!

32
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:38,480
Dolma, here. You drink the soup. I like cucumbers.

33
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:43,475
Xiao Hong, don’t eat the whole basket!

34
00:04:43,475 --> 00:04:48,080
Save some for Jiang Tao. He's loved cucumbers since childhood.

35
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:51,252
I picked extra just for him today.

36
00:04:51,252 --> 00:04:54,120
Auntie Tian, you really spoil Old Jiang!

37
00:04:54,120 --> 00:05:00,230
Oh! Professor Wen!

38
00:05:00,230 --> 00:05:02,350
Come, have a bowl!

39
00:05:02,350 --> 00:05:05,360
Professor Wen, you’re this old and still working with everyone?

40
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:08,620
Just getting some exercise!

41
00:05:08,620 --> 00:05:15,920
Your open-door education really reaches us poor peasants.

42
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:16,660
Here,

43
00:05:18,740 --> 00:05:25,770
Ever since foreign experts designed this dam, the reservoir filled up with silt.

44
00:05:25,770 --> 00:05:30,487
Hundreds of thousands of acres of farmland turned salty.

45
00:05:30,487 --> 00:05:34,970
We can’t grow grain or contribute to the country.

46
00:05:34,970 --> 00:05:40,500
It hurts us poor and lower-middle peasants deeply.

47
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:44,060
Professor Wen: Yes, that’s true.

48
00:05:44,060 --> 00:05:48,240
Auntie Tian: Since Jiang Tao brought you teachers and students here,

49
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:54,170
you’ve worked with laborers through wind and rain.

50
00:05:54,170 --> 00:05:59,200
All with one goal—to control the reservoir’s silt.

51
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:03,110
That’s good education from your school!

52
00:06:03,110 --> 00:06:06,380
Professor Wen: Auntie, we still haven’t done enough.

53
00:06:06,380 --> 00:06:08,690
Please guide us more.

54
00:06:08,690 --> 00:06:11,825
Auntie Tian: Guide you?

55
00:06:12,268 --> 00:06:16,685
I just can’t bear to see you leave! Ha ha ha!

56
00:06:19,609 --> 00:06:22,580
Zhong Dachuang: What? Leave?

57
00:06:23,027 --> 00:06:29,790
Auntie Tian: Last night, a few of us stayed up making these.

58
00:06:29,790 --> 00:06:33,650
They’re souvenirs—one for each of you!

59
00:06:33,650 --> 00:06:37,310
Dolma: They’re beautiful!

60
00:06:38,444 --> 00:06:42,820
Zhong Dachuang: "We must do a good job in managing the Yellow River."

61
00:06:43,164 --> 00:06:45,210
Soil?

62
00:06:45,284 --> 00:06:48,570
Auntie, what is this?

63
00:06:49,953 --> 00:06:53,228
Auntie Tian: This is soil from the Yellow River.

64
00:06:53,473 --> 00:07:02,311
It holds poor people’s tears, martyrs’ blood, and peasants’ sweat!

65
00:07:02,493 --> 00:07:08,817
Wherever you go, never forget the Yellow River!

66
00:07:09,143 --> 00:07:16,633
Zhong Dachuang: Auntie, after graduation, we won’t leave! We’ll take root right here!

67
00:07:17,166 --> 00:07:20,182
Auntie Tian: Really?  Everyone: Really!

68
00:07:20,251 --> 00:07:23,260
Auntie Tian: That’s wonderful!

69
00:07:23,260 --> 00:07:28,652
Shen Niu: This is our application to the Party committee. We ask to become peasants after graduation!

70
00:07:33,078 --> 00:07:40,222
Qiao Boren: Look at this—open-door education, and they don’t even want to study!

71
00:07:40,382 --> 00:07:44,810
College graduates becoming workers and peasants? Hmph!

72
00:07:44,970 --> 00:07:47,121
Professor Xue: College graduates as workers and peasants? Ha!

73
00:07:47,279 --> 00:07:49,702
Then why go to college at all?

74
00:07:49,737 --> 00:07:54,406
Yao Mingli: Director Qiao! Professor Xue!

75
00:07:54,430 --> 00:07:54,911
Qiao Boren: Mingli, where have you been?

76
00:07:55,095 --> 00:07:59,903
Yao Mingli: The Provincial Water Resources Bureau transferred me back.

77
00:08:00,015 --> 00:08:01,078
Qiao Boren: Great! Great! Ha ha ha!

78
00:08:01,102 --> 00:08:05,847
Professor Xue: Congratulations on ending your sent-down labor.

79
00:08:05,944 --> 00:08:11,636
Yao Mingli: Thank you. Goodbye.

80
00:08:11,666 --> 00:08:14,167
Qiao Boren: Wasn’t he your top student back then?

81
00:08:14,199 --> 00:08:22,362
Professor Xue: Yes, but Jiang Tao labeled him ideologically reactionary, a typical "bourgeois expert."  He was even struggled against for it!

82
00:08:22,655 --> 00:08:27,763
Honestly, he just read more books.

83
00:08:27,821 --> 00:08:33,566
Today’s students aren’t even half his level.

84
00:08:35,728 --> 00:08:38,049
Dolma: Comrade Jiang Tao,

85
00:08:38,183 --> 00:08:44,822
the cuckoo flies to announce spring,

86
00:08:44,967 --> 00:08:51,212
our words to the Party express sincere wishes.

87
00:08:51,424 --> 00:08:53,229
Jiang Tao: Dolma!

88
00:08:53,395 --> 00:09:02,864
The Yellow River’s depth shows in its waves. A freed serf’s wishes show in action!

89
00:09:03,154 --> 00:09:07,253
My students, you are all messengers of spring!

90
00:09:07,474 --> 00:09:13,186
After storms, flowers will bloom!

91
00:09:13,501 --> 00:09:23,190
I support you. Post them!

92
00:09:24,163 --> 00:09:28,774
Qiao Boren: Old Jiang, look at those big-character posters!

93
00:09:30,027 --> 00:09:33,189
Talking about becoming workers and peasants after graduation!

94
00:09:33,345 --> 00:09:36,129
As leaders, we must guide them in the right direction!

95
00:09:36,421 --> 00:09:39,920
Jiang Tao: Ha ha ha!

96
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:43,477
Old Qiao, the students wrote them well!

97
00:09:43,477 --> 00:09:48,555
While the Soviet Union tempts youth with privilege,

98
00:09:48,638 --> 00:09:55,006
our worker-peasant-soldier students willingly stand with workers and peasants.

99
00:09:55,328 --> 00:09:58,425
This is unprecedented in education history!

100
00:09:58,644 --> 00:10:04,771
This is an encouraging achievement of studying Marxist theory and criticizing bourgeois right!

101
00:10:04,874 --> 00:10:10,548
Qiao Boren: Jiang Tao, you’re head of the worker propaganda team, Party secretary, and a provincial standing committee member.

102
00:10:10,716 --> 00:10:13,651
You surely know more than we do.

103
00:10:13,818 --> 00:10:17,475
I hear education is about to be “rectified”?

104
00:10:17,526 --> 00:10:19,403
Professor Xue: Hmph!

105
00:10:19,427 --> 00:10:21,690
Jiang Tao: Oh? You’re very sensitive.

106
00:10:27,903 --> 00:10:30,215
Qiao Boren: It's me, Qiao Boren!

107
00:10:30,615 --> 00:10:33,183
Oh—Secretary Song?

108
00:10:34,417 --> 00:10:35,995
What?

109
00:10:37,213 --> 00:10:38,281
Ah?

110
00:10:38,351 --> 00:10:42,291
Excellent! Excellent!

111
00:10:42,362 --> 00:10:44,195
Qiao Boren: Han Xiaofang, come here!

112
00:10:45,028 --> 00:10:48,268
Your father has been reinstated!

113
00:10:48,319 --> 00:10:50,931
Still the First Party Secretary of the province!

114
00:10:50,955 --> 00:10:52,950
Han Xiaofang: Hey!

115
00:10:52,974 --> 00:10:55,399
Qiao Boren: Tomorrow afternoon, the two o’clock flight!

116
00:11:07,676 --> 00:11:12,286
Han Ling: Ha ha ha ha ha!

117
00:11:12,402 --> 00:11:16,661
Comrade Deng Xiaoping invited me to dinner at his home.

118
00:11:16,739 --> 00:11:22,344
He said that after the Cultural Revolution, everything needs rectification.

119
00:11:22,447 --> 00:11:27,361
He told us old fellows: dare to act, and don't be afraid!

120
00:11:27,385 --> 00:11:29,324
Qiao Boren: Ha ha ha!

121
00:11:29,348 --> 00:11:32,091
These eight or nine years weren’t easy.

122
00:11:32,115 --> 00:11:39,277
Han Ling: Indeed. Green hills never age, and clear waters flow eternally. Aren’t I back again?

123
00:11:39,301 --> 00:11:41,721
Qiao Boren: Ha ha ha ha ha!

124
00:11:41,745 --> 00:11:48,605
Han Ling: Xiaoping said rectification must faithfully follow the “three directives.”

125
00:11:48,629 --> 00:11:51,639
Qiao Boren: Great! Education really should be rectified!

126
00:11:51,663 --> 00:11:59,823
Han Ling: Transport, science, and the Four Modernizations all depend on education. Education must not hold them back.

127
00:12:01,424 --> 00:12:12,415
Xiaoping values education greatly. He said the biggest danger now is not studying. Education is where we must start.

128
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:14,098
Qiao Boren: Start with education?!

129
00:12:14,140 --> 00:12:17,982
Han Ling: Yes. Think carefully about it.

130
00:12:18,188 --> 00:12:27,206
Where did the Cultural Revolution begin, Old Qiao? You must have courage!

131
00:12:27,447 --> 00:12:29,447
Ha ha ha.

132
00:12:29,636 --> 00:12:31,655
Qiao Boren: But what about Jiang Tao at our university?

133
00:12:31,679 --> 00:12:38,682
Han Ling: Don’t worry. The situation is different now. No stone is too hard to block our road!

134
00:12:40,241 --> 00:12:43,761
Lyrics: Facing the bright sun, bearing the Party’s hopes,

135
00:12:43,785 --> 00:12:48,335
Song (lyrics): we worker-peasant-soldier students come from across the motherland…

136
00:12:48,359 --> 00:12:54,069
Han Ling: This is a university? These are college students? Reverse, now!

137
00:12:54,204 --> 00:13:00,774
Secretary Song, notify an emergency provincial meeting! Fully implement Comrade Xiaoping’s directives!

138
00:13:00,947 --> 00:13:04,910
Secretary Song: Yes.

139
00:13:07,970 --> 00:13:12,180
Secretary Song: Let me handle this.

140
00:13:12,299 --> 00:13:17,835
Han Ling: This is outrageous! This approach doesn’t reflect the new spirit. It must be rectified!

141
00:13:17,890 --> 00:13:20,552
Old Old Huang, Today’s meeting was too tense.

142
00:13:20,688 --> 00:13:21,646
Yeah.

143
00:13:21,764 --> 00:13:25,831
Sister Zhao and Jiang Tao’s opinions deserve serious attention.

144
00:13:25,995 --> 00:13:33,125
But rectification and the Three Directives were brought back from Beijing by Party Secretary Han.

145
00:13:33,580 --> 00:13:36,980
Jiang Tao: Sister Zhao, I didn’t expect this wind to blow so fiercely.

146
00:13:37,135 --> 00:13:42,645
Sister Zhao: Yes. Your speech at the meeting was absolutely right.

147
00:13:42,740 --> 00:13:47,730
Jiang Tao: If rectification goes this way, won’t it erase all the gains of the Cultural Revolution?

148
00:13:49,289 --> 00:13:56,739
Sister Zhao: This is fundamentally about one’s attitude toward the Cultural Revolution itself.

149
00:13:56,812 --> 00:14:02,071
Han Ling: Hmph! What should be rectified must be rectified!

150
00:14:10,221 --> 00:14:17,670
Sister Zhao: Your university will be hit first again.
You must be fully prepared.

151
00:14:17,694 --> 00:14:22,094
Jiang Tao: Don’t worry, Sister Zhao. I’m heading back. Goodbye.

152
00:16:17,944 --> 00:16:25,261
Han Ling: Secretary Song? Why doesn’t the dripping water sound as clear as before?

153
00:16:25,349 --> 00:16:27,610
Secretary Song: I’ll check it.

154
00:16:27,801 --> 00:16:33,911
Xiao Lin! Xiao Lin!

155
00:16:33,935 --> 00:16:43,021
How did you adjust this dripping sound? Don’t you know Party Secretary Han can’t sleep if it’s wrong? Fix it immediately!

156
00:16:43,046 --> 00:16:45,663
Secretary Song, where should the sofa go?

157
00:16:45,688 --> 00:16:50,067
Secretary Song: Here. Put it here.

158
00:16:50,459 --> 00:16:54,389
Han Ling: No! Put it exactly where it was before the Cultural Revolution!

159
00:16:54,423 --> 00:16:58,306
Oh, put it there, there.

160
00:17:01,393 --> 00:17:06,236
Secretary Song: Party Secretary Han, Director Qiao and Professor Xue are here.

161
00:17:06,298 --> 00:17:10,938
Han Ling: Old Xue, you’ve heard about rectifying education, right?

162
00:17:11,109 --> 00:17:17,251
Professor Xue: Ha ha. Just rumors.  Qiao Boren: Ha ha. I sensed something.

163
00:17:17,275 --> 00:17:21,247
Han Ling: Human intuition is powerful.

164
00:17:22,219 --> 00:17:27,153
Han Xiaofang: Uncle Qiao, Professor Xue, Dad.

165
00:17:27,177 --> 00:17:33,299
Han Ling: So, how has my worker-peasant-soldier student progressed lately?

166
00:17:33,323 --> 00:17:37,953
Han Xiaofang: We studied theory of dictatorship of the proletariat, and joined class struggle in factories and villages.

167
00:17:38,138 --> 00:17:41,226
Han Ling: I didn’t ask you that!

168
00:17:41,307 --> 00:17:47,607
Han Xiaofang: Oh. We criticized knowledge privatization and elitism. We vowed to become ordinary laborers.

169
00:17:47,631 --> 00:17:52,342
Han Ling: I’m asking about basic theory!

170
00:17:52,366 --> 00:17:56,889
Fluid mechanics. Materials mechanics. Quantum mechanics. How far have you gotten?

171
00:17:57,028 --> 00:18:03,403
Han Xiaofang: Comrade Jiang Tao said combining theory with sediment control helps us remember and apply it better.

172
00:18:04,307 --> 00:18:11,184
Han Ling: Better? This is complete chaos!

173
00:18:12,369 --> 00:18:22,168
If college students all become workers and peasants,
why run universities at all?

174
00:18:22,377 --> 00:18:27,361
It sounds revolutionary, but it’s pure petty-bourgeois fanaticism!

175
00:18:27,385 --> 00:18:34,370
Professor Xue: Yes, yes! Secretary Han is absolutely right!

176
00:18:34,395 --> 00:18:43,039
Qiao Boren: Exactly! Secretary Han, the responsibility isn’t on Xiaofang. Xiaofang has been working hard in his studies.

177
00:18:43,395 --> 00:18:47,645
Xue Yaozong: Right, right! It’s Jiang Tao’s fault, hmph!

178
00:18:48,186 --> 00:18:53,106
Han Ling: Hmm, from now on, listen more to Uncle Qiao and Professor Xue!

179
00:18:53,184 --> 00:18:54,513
Ha ha ha ha!

180
00:18:54,537 --> 00:18:57,622
Professor Xue: Alright, alright! Come eat some apples!

181
00:18:57,646 --> 00:19:02,861
Han Ling: Xiaofang, how much is this big apple in the store?

182
00:19:03,046 --> 00:19:04,486
Han Xiaofang: Forty cents per pound.

183
00:19:09,875 --> 00:19:11,555
Han Ling: And the small one?

184
00:19:11,579 --> 00:19:13,149
Han Xiaofang: Twenty cents.

185
00:19:13,173 --> 00:19:22,386
Han Ling: All apples, but different prices. How can college students equal workers and peasants, hmph!

186
00:19:25,784 --> 00:19:30,255
Education must be rectified!

187
00:19:30,473 --> 00:19:38,138
Qiao Boren: Hmm! I think rectification should start with investigating teaching quality.

188
00:19:38,434 --> 00:19:40,578
Han Ling: Good!

189
00:19:40,695 --> 00:19:45,335
Qiao Boren: Tomorrow, I’ll recall all open-door education students back!

190
00:20:12,649 --> 00:20:27,180
PA: Students, stop and don’t leave! Gather in the main building classroom immediately! Gather in the main building classroom immediately!

191
00:20:32,932 --> 00:20:39,627
Chatter

192
00:20:45,859 --> 00:20:48,720
Xiao Hong: Hey, Dachuang, what meeting is this?

193
00:20:48,744 --> 00:20:52,004
Zhong Dachuang: Don’t know. Professor Wen, do you know?

194
00:20:52,028 --> 00:20:53,481
Professor Wen: Don’t know.

195
00:20:53,505 --> 00:21:03,157
Qiao Boren: Students, quiet! Sit down! Sit down! Be quiet!

196
00:21:05,070 --> 00:21:12,545
Following the provincial leaders’ instructions, to implement the new spirit of education rectification,

197
00:21:12,570 --> 00:21:23,608
we will first investigate teaching quality. Students, time to take a surprise test!

198
00:21:35,926 --> 00:21:39,502
Professor Wen: Why didn’t the Party committee discuss this first?

199
00:21:39,763 --> 00:21:41,572
Professor Wen, Professor Wen. Going to be an exam?

200
00:21:41,596 --> 00:21:48,006
Qiao Boren: Instructor Zhou, please come forward.

201
00:21:48,210 --> 00:21:51,254
Instructor Zhou, distribute the exam papers to everyone.

202
00:21:51,279 --> 00:21:52,429
Um...

203
00:21:52,531 --> 00:21:56,775
Hmm? Go ahead, go ahead!

204
00:21:58,197 --> 00:22:03,659
Professor Xue: Heh heh, let’s do it together.

205
00:22:23,974 --> 00:22:28,621
Professor Wen: Old Xue, who made these questions?

206
00:22:28,870 --> 00:22:30,413
Professor Xue: What?

207
00:22:30,437 --> 00:22:35,402
Professor Wen: Isn’t this basically the same detached approach from before the Cultural Revolution?

208
00:22:35,426 --> 00:22:38,861
Professor Xue: Director Qiao said this is the province’s idea.

209
00:22:40,786 --> 00:22:45,031
Qiao Boren: Alright, no talking!

210
00:22:45,299 --> 00:22:50,695
Now announcing exam rules!

211
00:22:51,345 --> 00:23:05,365
One: No whispering. Two: No looking at books. Three: No extending exam time!

212
00:23:10,714 --> 00:23:13,526
Xiao Hong: Dachuang, did the Party committee discuss this?

213
00:23:14,754 --> 00:23:17,203
Zhong Dachuang: Go find Old Jiang quickly!

214
00:23:53,549 --> 00:23:56,124
(Why is this?)

215
00:24:01,090 --> 00:24:05,228
Professor Xue: Keep yourself together! This is an exam!

216
00:24:14,469 --> 00:24:20,171
Zhong Dachuang: This is a surprise attack! Students, let’s find the Party committee!

217
00:24:20,576 --> 00:24:22,903
Hey, hey hey!?

218
00:24:26,870 --> 00:24:34,290
Qiao Boren: Zhong Dachuang! As a Party committee member, you lead a charge against the exam and disrupt education rectification!

219
00:24:34,725 --> 00:24:37,235
Who are you targeting?

220
00:24:37,259 --> 00:24:39,878
Zhong Dachuang: Whoever backtracks, we aim at them!

221
00:24:39,902 --> 00:24:50,229
Jiang Tao: Well said!  Dachuang’s question deserves thought!

222
00:24:50,485 --> 00:24:52,065
Ha ha.

223
00:24:52,089 --> 00:24:58,790
Old Qiao, doesn’t this exam show problems? Shouldn’t everyone fully express opinions?

224
00:24:58,814 --> 00:25:08,924
Professor Wen: Let me speak. This exam is indeed similar to criticized methods during the Cultural Revolution.

225
00:25:10,186 --> 00:25:22,048
Professor Xue: Oh? Professor Wen, if we connect this exam to denying the Cultural Revolution, others can’t speak!

226
00:25:22,072 --> 00:25:29,190
Qiao Boren: We should face reality. Teaching quality is low, just admit it.

227
00:25:30,243 --> 00:25:35,683
We just need to take real measures to rectify and catch up!

228
00:25:39,256 --> 00:25:46,856
Can’t answer? So you quit the exam? Hmph! That doesn’t solve the problem, right?

229
00:25:47,214 --> 00:25:50,044
Professor Xue: Right, right! Exactly!

230
00:25:51,180 --> 00:26:00,550
If learning is solid and foundations are strong, why fear exams?

231
00:26:03,429 --> 00:26:08,098
Jiang Tao: Fear exams?

232
00:26:08,556 --> 00:26:16,996
Qiao Boren: Comrade Wang Jian, as deputy Party secretary and veteran educator, how can you agree with Jiang Tao’s action?

233
00:26:18,001 --> 00:26:24,561
Wang Jian, Deputy Party Secretary of Yellow River University: Old Qiao, this is not Jiang Tao’s personal opinion. This is the Party committee’s resolution.

234
00:26:25,712 --> 00:26:28,452
Qiao Boren: Fine, fine, I reserve my opinion!

235
00:26:29,096 --> 00:26:34,116
Yaozong, aren’t you feeling unwell? Don’t go!

236
00:26:34,140 --> 00:26:47,958
Professor Xue: I must go. Today is the professors’ meeting. Since the Cultural Revolution, it’s the first of its kind. I must attend!

237
00:26:48,121 --> 00:26:58,469
(Chatter)

238
00:27:00,330 --> 00:27:13,055
Jiang Tao: Comrades, recently fierce debates arose around this exam at our university. Everyone knows the situation.

239
00:27:14,883 --> 00:27:22,663
Allegedly, this exam is meant to investigate teaching quality and implement education rectification.

240
00:27:22,834 --> 00:27:26,844
Since it’s an investigation, it must be comprehensive.

241
00:27:28,276 --> 00:27:29,897
[Agreed voices]

242
00:27:30,131 --> 00:27:38,412
So, after research by the Party committee, today we will also have all present comrades take an exam.

243
00:27:40,369 --> 00:28:01,303
(Discontent voices)

244
00:28:04,578 --> 00:28:15,370
The exam questions are fair and reasonable. We’ll reuse last students’ questions. Students, distribute the papers!

245
00:28:28,671 --> 00:28:34,491
Professor Xue: What? We didn't have time to prepare!

246
00:28:34,615 --> 00:28:40,218
Zhong Dachuang: Ha ha, if you study well and have strong foundations, no need to prepare.

247
00:28:43,069 --> 00:28:48,429
Jiang Tao: Alright, teachers, quiet please. Announcing exam rules:

248
00:28:49,918 --> 00:28:59,778
One, no whispering; Two, no looking at books; Three, no extending exam time.

249
00:29:59,410 --> 00:30:05,379
Professor Wen (writing a poem): Sudden news of exams shocks the heart,

250
00:30:05,512 --> 00:30:09,795
Looking back, yet unaware,

251
00:30:09,977 --> 00:30:14,436
The path returns to correct,

252
00:30:14,561 --> 00:30:20,691
Educational revolution forever green.

253
00:30:22,455 --> 00:30:27,862
Jiang Tao: Alright, comrades, now I announce:

254
00:30:28,267 --> 00:30:33,355
No matter how well you did on the exam, you can keep being professors.

255
00:30:33,604 --> 00:30:38,160
This one exam alone can’t measure your real abilities.

256
00:30:38,362 --> 00:30:45,352
But it proves that the revisionist education path and teaching methods are extremely foolish.

257
00:30:46,498 --> 00:30:51,021
Heh, some say this makes comrades look bad.

258
00:30:51,068 --> 00:31:00,770
Hmph, no. Just taking part in this exam is itself a critique of the revisionist education path.

259
00:31:02,642 --> 00:31:12,551
It reminds me of something that happened thirteen years ago, also in this classroom…

260
00:31:53,935 --> 00:31:59,738
Students: Xiao Hua? What happened? Are you okay?

261
00:31:59,762 --> 00:32:01,982
Go back! Don’t take the exam!

262
00:32:02,098 --> 00:32:03,638
A student: If you don’t take it, you’ll fail the year!

263
00:32:03,840 --> 00:32:05,420
Another student: Fail? You’ll be expelled!

264
00:32:05,444 --> 00:32:11,124
Professor Xue.

265
00:32:11,303 --> 00:32:16,961
Jiang Tao: Someone, take Xiao Hua to the infirmary now!

266
00:32:21,706 --> 00:32:28,647
Professor Xue: Alright, sit down, everyone! Sit down! The exam continues!

267
00:32:30,442 --> 00:32:32,442
Professor Xue.

268
00:32:33,254 --> 00:32:58,441
Jiang Tao: This is inhumane! It destroys youth! Let’s take it to the Party committee!

269
00:33:00,522 --> 00:33:06,170
Principal Qiao! I protest! You don’t care about students’ lives!

270
00:33:06,334 --> 00:33:13,914
A surprise attack, sending so many worker-peasant transfer students away! I protest!

271
00:33:15,250 --> 00:33:20,064
Qiao Boren: Jiang Tao! I announce: starting today,

272
00:33:20,088 --> 00:33:24,878
you are no longer a student of our college. Leave immediately!

273
00:33:28,551 --> 00:33:35,471
Student: Jiang Tao! Jiang Tao! Why?

274
00:33:35,495 --> 00:33:39,005
The factory only sent three of us to college.

275
00:33:39,105 --> 00:33:47,495
If you admit fault to Principal Qiao, you can stay. Our future here is bright!

276
00:33:48,435 --> 00:33:56,625
Jiang Tao: Admit fault? They forced Liu Xiaohua to death! This school is not a place for us!

277
00:34:03,317 --> 00:34:10,917
Think carefully: thirteen years have passed, yet these two exams are exactly the same!

278
00:34:13,673 --> 00:34:21,263
This shows the bourgeoisie trying to replay history’s lesson. We must never allow it!

279
00:34:23,109 --> 00:34:29,884
Everyone, think about what this exam really means!

280
00:34:30,662 --> 00:34:36,702
Isn’t it a denial of the direction of the education revolution? Reversing the verdicts of the Cultural Revolution!

281
00:34:39,290 --> 00:34:41,790
Shen Niu!

282
00:34:42,001 --> 00:34:42,821
Dolma!

283
00:34:44,997 --> 00:34:47,361
Dolma: Xiao Hong! Why didn’t you catch it?

284
00:34:48,000 --> 00:34:49,480
Xiao Hong: Th-this… I wasn’t ready!

285
00:34:49,791 --> 00:34:51,851
Students: Ha ha ha ha!

286
00:34:51,875 --> 00:34:58,695
Zhong Dachuang: Hmph, if you study well and have solid foundations, no need to prepare!

287
00:34:59,845 --> 00:35:02,905
Catch it!

288
00:35:02,929 --> 00:35:04,969
Students: Instructor Zhou! Instructor Zhou!

289
00:35:06,284 --> 00:35:12,224
Sister Zhao: Comrade Jiang Tao, you’ve implemented the new spirit well!

290
00:35:12,504 --> 00:35:20,365
Even failing doesn’t matter. A circle shows learning, we just need to give them more support!

291
00:35:20,389 --> 00:35:27,599
Jiang Tao: Yes, Sister Zhao. The bourgeoisie struck at us, but we blocked it. They won’t be satisfied.

292
00:35:27,902 --> 00:35:34,127
Sister Zhao: Of course, class struggle is getting more complex.

293
00:35:34,151 --> 00:35:40,538
We must watch out for people in our Party sitting on the same bench as the bourgeoisie!

294
00:35:40,562 --> 00:35:44,757
Jiang Tao: Oh, why so happy?

295
00:35:44,781 --> 00:35:48,493
Students: We repelled the bourgeois attack! Of course we’re happy!

296
00:35:48,517 --> 00:35:52,584
We welcome you and Director Zhao to join our victory celebration!

297
00:35:52,608 --> 00:35:57,302
Jiang Tao: Victory should certainly be celebrated.

298
00:35:57,653 --> 00:36:05,230
But this is just a small skirmish, comrades, when the proletariat faces a sudden bourgeois attack!

299
00:36:05,254 --> 00:36:06,814
Students: Good! Keep fighting!

300
00:36:06,838 --> 00:36:09,955
Come on! Move!

301
00:36:09,979 --> 00:36:13,562
Sister Zhao: We must uphold the direction of the education revolution and develop this great momentum!

302
00:36:13,586 --> 00:36:19,246
Jiang Tao: Right. Tomorrow, return the students to the open-door education points.

303
00:36:30,740 --> 00:36:35,271
Instructor Zhou: Goodbye, Comrade Wang Jian. Old Jiang.

304
00:36:35,295 --> 00:36:40,119
Jiang Tao: We must focus on students’ political thinking.

305
00:36:40,143 --> 00:36:43,653
Once at the worksite, make sure to talk with Xiaofang.

306
00:36:44,051 --> 00:36:46,171
Instructor Zhou: Okay, goodbye!

307
00:38:01,517 --> 00:38:04,457
Han Ling: What dance was that just now?

308
00:38:04,644 --> 00:38:06,604
Qiao Boren: “Amei Goes to College.”

309
00:38:06,712 --> 00:38:08,190
Han Ling: Which Amei?

310
00:38:08,455 --> 00:38:12,861
Qiao Boren: Heh, a Miao village girl.

311
00:38:14,479 --> 00:38:17,597
Han Ling: Did she pass the exam? Huh?

312
00:38:17,621 --> 00:38:21,381
Qiao Boren: Exam? Hmph! The first shot went off crooked!

313
00:38:22,104 --> 00:38:42,704
Han Ling: Not crooked. The whole rectification only needs to follow Comrade Xiaoping’s “Three Directives,” Even a crooked shot can hit the mark.

314
00:38:43,256 --> 00:38:49,352
And the press? Has the newspaper editor come?  Secretary Song: He's here.

315
00:38:49,907 --> 00:38:51,518
Please.


316
00:39:00,712 --> 00:39:11,256
Secretary Song: Party Secretary Han’s youngest daughter has been in the countryside for nearly a year. She’s very mindful of political impact, never mentions…

317
00:39:11,692 --> 00:39:16,002
Qiao Boren: No problem! She’ll go to college this year!

318
00:39:16,026 --> 00:39:20,456
Secretary Song: My son happens to be in the same production team as her.

319
00:39:20,480 --> 00:39:22,732
Qiao Boren: Together, then. Do it together.

320
00:39:22,756 --> 00:39:28,604
Newspaper Editor: Here’s the editorial, titled “Education Must Be Rectified, On Taking the Three Directives as the Key Link.”

321
00:39:28,628 --> 00:39:30,215
Han Ling: Mm hmm.

322
00:39:30,239 --> 00:39:38,072
Newspaper Editor: And this is Xiaofang’s big-character poster, “College Students Must Contribute Greatly,” ready to post together tomorrow.

323
00:39:38,096 --> 00:39:44,486
Han Ling: Remove Xiaofang’s name. Replace with “Yellow River College Worker-Peasant-Soldier Students.”

324
00:39:44,510 --> 00:39:49,840
Newspaper Editor: Okay, good. Next: article two on industry,

325
00:39:49,864 --> 00:39:53,966
article three on agriculture, four on science, five on arts.

326
00:39:54,485 --> 00:40:00,912
Han Ling: Posting so many editorials? You don’t understand the art of struggle.

327
00:40:00,936 --> 00:40:07,664
Some issues can be published under the Worker-Peasant-Soldier name.

328
00:40:07,688 --> 00:40:10,598
The goal is comprehensive rectification.

329
00:40:12,090 --> 00:40:19,300
Newspaper Editor: Comrade Han Ling, the People’s Daily and Red Flag magazine never publicized that the Three Directives are the Key Link for comprehensive rectification…

330
00:40:19,324 --> 00:40:24,364
Han Ling: What are you afraid of? Comrade Xiaoping’s instructions aren’t valid?

331
00:40:25,582 --> 00:40:30,934
Also, add this meaning:

332
00:40:31,136 --> 00:40:38,926
Poor education is due to leaders and some people opposing the Party line!

333
00:40:40,155 --> 00:40:43,448
That’s the message. Print it tomorrow!

334
00:40:43,472 --> 00:40:46,316
Ha ha ha ha ha ha!

335
00:40:46,340 --> 00:40:50,000
Professor Xue: Ah, the situation is excellent!

336
00:40:50,024 --> 00:40:51,334
Qiao Boren: Indeed!

337
00:40:51,358 --> 00:40:56,888
Professor Xue: After these eight or nine years, our time has finally come!

338
00:40:56,912 --> 00:41:00,222
Qiao Boren: Ha ha ha ha!

339
00:41:00,246 --> 00:41:07,483
These eight or nine years, we ran fast, caught up with errors!

340
00:41:07,507 --> 00:41:12,650
Ran slow? The errors caught up with us!

341
00:41:13,977 --> 00:41:15,977
Sigh...

342
00:41:18,028 --> 00:41:21,829
Eight or nine years…

343
00:41:23,765 --> 00:41:36,745
Professor Xue: Yellow River source, your youth has returned!

344
00:41:46,085 --> 00:41:52,015
Zhong Dachuang: Han Xiaofang, tell me, what exactly are we rectifying? Why? Where?

345
00:41:52,039 --> 00:41:53,995
Xiao Hong: Tell us! Tell us!

346
00:41:54,020 --> 00:41:59,460
Han Xiaofang: There’s so much to fix! Open-door education, all this chaos!

347
00:41:59,484 --> 00:42:02,939
College students graduating to become workers and peasants? Totally extreme left!

348
00:42:02,963 --> 00:42:04,763
Xiao Hong: Oh, afraid of being like a twenty-cent apple!

349
00:42:05,260 --> 00:42:06,211
Ha ha ha!

350
00:42:06,235 --> 00:42:08,355
Han Xiaofang: Why not?

351
00:42:08,379 --> 00:42:11,279
College students can’t be equated with ordinary workers and peasants!

352
00:42:11,303 --> 00:42:17,953
Instructor Zhou: Xiaofang, you’ve always said:

353
00:42:17,977 --> 00:42:22,929
Learn from workers and peasants. They are the masters of the country.

354
00:42:22,953 --> 00:42:28,331
How is it today that you use the price of goods to explain human relationships?

355
00:42:28,355 --> 00:42:31,955
And compare yourself with workers and peasants as forty-cent and twenty-cent apples?

356
00:42:31,979 --> 00:42:36,272
Don’t you feel ashamed? Where did you even pick up this nonsense?

357
00:42:36,577 --> 00:42:39,027
Han Xiaofang: The new spirit from the Central Committee, do you understand?

358
00:42:39,946 --> 00:42:42,586
Dolma: What new spirit? Isn’t it just your father’s spirit?

359
00:42:42,610 --> 00:42:48,490
Shen Niu: Hmph, the once-famous capitalist roader in the province, I see, hasn’t changed much!

360
00:42:49,708 --> 00:42:54,928
Han Xiaofang: What? You dare oppose the spirit of rectification? And slander veteran cadres? You?

361
00:42:55,847 --> 00:43:05,890
Shen Niu: I ask you, do the May 7th Directive, the July 21st Directive, and Chairman Mao’s long-standing teachings still count?

362
00:43:05,914 --> 00:43:07,894
Han Xiaofang: Now the Three Directives are the core!

363
00:43:09,638 --> 00:43:11,876
Shen Niu: Three Directives as the Key Link?

364
00:43:11,900 --> 00:43:16,220
Instructor Zhou: The provincial paper says the Three Directives are the Key Link. I don’t quite agree.

365
00:43:16,244 --> 00:43:21,074
Professor Wen: Yes, for some people, they do whatever the Cultural Revolution criticized,

366
00:43:21,098 --> 00:43:25,968
and oppose whatever the Cultural Revolution supported. Truly worthless!

367
00:43:25,992 --> 00:43:27,295
Speaking of, has Jiang Tao gone home recently?

368
00:43:27,319 --> 00:43:30,799
Instructor Zhou: Yes, and he asked about our factory too.

369
00:43:35,788 --> 00:43:44,768
Flattop: My fellow workers, have you read the papers recently? Open-door education has many problems!

370
00:43:44,792 --> 00:43:53,572
The Provincial Committee says Yellow River College's sediment discharge plan lacks scientific basis!

371
00:43:53,596 --> 00:43:58,346
So the gate-lifting equipment will not be built!

372
00:43:58,990 --> 00:44:02,102
Workers: Then what about the sediment in the reservoir?

373
00:44:02,336 --> 00:44:06,466
Flattop: The Provincial Committee decided to import dredgers for sand removal.

374
00:44:06,808 --> 00:44:10,226
Instructor Zhou: Wasn’t that the plan criticized during the Cultural Revolution?

375
00:44:10,250 --> 00:44:13,722
Flattop: I don’t know! It’s the province’s decision!

376
00:44:13,746 --> 00:44:17,294
Workers: The province’s decision is wrong!

377
00:44:18,081 --> 00:44:23,291
Professor Wen: Comrades, they want to hit two targets with one shot!

378
00:44:23,315 --> 00:44:30,805
One is to stop the factory's production, the other is to end the education revolution.

379
00:44:30,829 --> 00:44:33,572
Which is Impossible!

380
00:44:33,938 --> 00:44:39,846
Comrades, let’s keep working!

381
00:45:02,102 --> 00:45:10,062
Jiang Tao: They completely deny that human history over thousands of years is a history of class struggle;

382
00:45:12,029 --> 00:45:17,469
They deny the proletariat’s class struggle against the bourgeoisie;

383
00:45:20,436 --> 00:45:28,636
They deny the proletariat’s revolution and dictatorship over the bourgeoisie.

384
00:45:31,859 --> 00:45:33,357
Dad.

385
00:45:34,004 --> 00:45:36,616
Xiao Mei, why aren't you asleep?

386
00:45:36,640 --> 00:45:40,168
Xiao Mei: Daddy, come, I want to ask you something!

387
00:45:45,213 --> 00:45:47,313
What does “rectification” mean?

388
00:45:47,337 --> 00:45:50,147
Jiang Tao: Oh, Xiao Mei, who told you that?

389
00:45:50,514 --> 00:45:55,324
Xiao Mei: Our school teachers argued. Teacher Wang said rectification is good,

390
00:45:55,394 --> 00:45:59,654
Teacher Li said rectification is bad. So which is it?

391
00:45:59,678 --> 00:46:02,410
Jiang Tao: Oh, what do you think?

392
00:46:02,434 --> 00:46:03,902
Xiao Mei: I say it’s bad.

393
00:46:03,926 --> 00:46:10,993
Teacher Wang said, after rectification, when we grow up, we can go to college without going to the countryside.

394
00:46:11,017 --> 00:46:12,580
Jiang Tao: Alright, sleep now.

395
00:46:14,584 --> 00:46:20,884
Rectification is opposing what Chairman Mao said, resisting new things. Of course it’s bad.

396
00:46:21,056 --> 00:46:22,796
Xiao Mei: So you also oppose rectification?

397
00:46:22,820 --> 00:46:24,930
Jiang Tao: Yes, I oppose it too.

398
00:46:24,954 --> 00:46:26,444
Ha ha ha.

399
00:46:27,733 --> 00:46:30,473
Xiao Mei: Daddy, do you guys argue too?

400
00:46:30,497 --> 00:46:32,157
Jiang Tao: No, it’s struggle!

401
00:46:32,181 --> 00:46:34,021
Xiao Mei: Then I want to struggle too!

402
00:46:34,045 --> 00:46:36,937
Jiang Tao: Ha ha ha.

403
00:46:36,961 --> 00:46:41,329
Come in. Oh, Comrade Wang Jian! So late, still awake?

404
00:46:41,353 --> 00:46:42,833
Wang Jian: Weren’t you awake too?

405
00:46:42,858 --> 00:46:47,910
Jiang Tao: Ha ha ha ha, the bourgeoisie won’t let us sleep!

406
00:46:47,934 --> 00:46:50,528
Wang Jian: Secretary Song from the Provincial Committee called,

407
00:46:50,553 --> 00:46:54,273
asking us to reprint the provincial editorial and Xiaofang’s big-character poster in this issue.

408
00:46:54,298 --> 00:46:57,661
Jiang Tao: I've heard. How about your opinion?

409
00:46:58,243 --> 00:47:09,421
Wang Jian: I repeatedly studied Chairman Mao’s teachings, reviewed the path of the past eight or nine years, and I’m convinced their approach is wrong.

410
00:47:10,573 --> 00:47:16,080
But I don’t understand why they proposed the "Three Directives as the Key Link."

411
00:47:16,392 --> 00:47:20,935
Jiang Tao: At the beginning, I often wondered about this too.

412
00:47:21,121 --> 00:47:25,241
My head hurt thinking!

413
00:47:25,265 --> 00:47:30,945
I consulted Marx, Lenin, and Mao,

414
00:47:32,020 --> 00:47:38,140
and studied counter-examples like Bukharin, Khrushchev, Liu Shaoqi, Lin Biao.

415
00:47:41,418 --> 00:47:48,760
One exam, one provincial newspaper, made me clearly see:

416
00:47:49,149 --> 00:47:55,357
They raised the black flags of “class struggle extinguished” and “productive forces determinism" to attack us again.

417
00:47:56,135 --> 00:47:57,575
Wang Jian: You mean?

418
00:48:01,151 --> 00:48:07,368
Jiang Tao: Fully reprint the 16 May Notification and confront them directly!

419
00:48:07,392 --> 00:48:17,680
Wang Jian: Good. And Red Flag magazine, see! The article criticizing Song Jiang the surrenderist is very targeted.

420
00:48:18,798 --> 00:48:28,031
Jiang Tao: Also, select a few big-character posters from the worker-peasant-soldier students and publish them in this issue!

421
00:48:32,203 --> 00:48:33,483
Passerby: Hey, comrades, please line up.

422
00:48:33,507 --> 00:48:35,309
Instructor Zhou: Sorry, I have to catch a train.

423
00:48:35,333 --> 00:48:37,501
Newsstand Clerk: Comrade, here’s your change.

424
00:48:40,659 --> 00:48:45,821
Instructor Zhou: Why is the school journal publishing the 16 May Notification now? They must be up to something!

425
00:48:46,814 --> 00:48:50,606
To me, this goes against the provincial paper’s “Three Directives as the Key Link"!

426
00:48:51,440 --> 00:48:54,200
Flattop: Provincial Paper, anyone wants it?

427
00:48:54,224 --> 00:48:56,344
Anyone read the provincial paper? The provincial paper has the new spirit!

428
00:48:56,399 --> 00:48:58,831
Come on, comrades, read the paper!

429
00:48:58,855 --> 00:49:00,213
Hey, comrades, read the paper!

430
00:49:00,237 --> 00:49:01,927
The provincial paper is free! Free! 

431
00:49:01,951 --> 00:49:06,571
Hey, comrades, read the paper! Free!

432
00:49:06,595 --> 00:49:11,485
Song Secretary: Party Secretary Han, it’s chaos! Chaos! The whole city is in disorder!

433
00:49:11,509 --> 00:49:16,824
This is a provincial theoretical publication. What if it reaches Vice Premier Deng?

434
00:49:16,848 --> 00:49:19,543
Han Ling: Hmm? Any reaction?

435
00:49:19,567 --> 00:49:27,908
Song Secretary: Some say, when you compare the 16 May Notification with “Three Directives as the Key Link,” it seems off. It looks like someone wants to alter the Party’s line.

436
00:49:27,933 --> 00:49:31,513
Han Ling: Who? Who do they say wants to alter it?

437
00:49:31,537 --> 00:49:36,760
Song Secretary: They say the journal reprinted an article from Red Flag magazine, and people keep asking:

438
00:49:36,784 --> 00:49:38,914
Who are the modern surrenderists?

439
00:49:38,938 --> 00:49:41,840
Who, outside the 108 heroes of Liangshan, betrayed?

440
00:49:41,864 --> 00:49:46,246
Who turned the Hall of Rebellion into the Hall of Loyalty? Altering the Party’s line?

441
00:49:46,270 --> 00:49:50,175
Who accepted amnesty and then attacked Fang La, suppressing revolutionary rebels?

442
00:49:50,199 --> 00:49:54,128
Han Ling: Who, who? Don’t worry about the ancients!

443
00:49:59,282 --> 00:50:05,742
Now it’s about stability and unity. No surrenderists exist!

444
00:50:05,766 --> 00:50:14,891
Song Secretary: But publishing Chairman Mao’s comments now, the Water Margin instructions must have meaning. I worry…

445
00:50:15,134 --> 00:50:23,334
Han Ling: Overly sensitive! Your name is Song Bin, not Song Jiang!

446
00:50:23,358 --> 00:50:28,686
Go immediately to investigate the journal’s background.

447
00:50:28,710 --> 00:50:36,940
Anyone attacking the “Three Directives as the Key Link” must be strictly dealt with, firmly suppressed!

448
00:50:36,964 --> 00:50:43,174
Also, this issue of the journal must stop circulating immediately!

449
00:50:43,239 --> 00:50:47,839
Crowd: Why stop selling? Why stop selling?

450
00:50:47,863 --> 00:50:49,923
There must be copies here!

451
00:50:49,947 --> 00:50:51,122
Why stop?

452
00:50:51,146 --> 00:50:53,841
Students: Step aside, comrades, here comes the journal!

453
00:50:53,865 --> 00:51:04,033
Comrades, step aside. We’re delivering to the newsstand. If you want to buy, queue at the stand!

454
00:51:04,057 --> 00:51:05,077
Crowd: They’re not selling!

455
00:51:05,101 --> 00:51:08,288
See, they’ve hung the “Stop Selling” sign!

456
00:51:08,312 --> 00:51:15,560
Students: Not selling? Dachuang, let’s sell! Alright, we’ll sell!

457
00:51:17,929 --> 00:51:23,804
Yumei: Old Jiang! Old Jiang!

458
00:51:23,828 --> 00:51:27,628
Jiang Tao: Yumei? What’s the matter?

459
00:51:30,639 --> 00:51:35,389
Yumei: Old Jiang, the province removed Comrade Old Geng, Deputy Director of the Revolutionary Committee!

460
00:51:35,413 --> 00:51:38,365
They even said they might expel him from the Party!

461
00:51:38,389 --> 00:51:39,937
Jiang Tao: On what grounds?

462
00:51:39,962 --> 00:51:45,220
Yumei: Because Comrade old Geng led everyone to study a few articles reprinted in this issue of the journal,

463
00:51:45,244 --> 00:51:48,337
and raised different views on the “Three Directives as the Key Link.”

464
00:51:48,361 --> 00:51:52,941
Yumei: They claim old Geng incited workers, opposed the provincial committee, opposed the Party, opposed the Central Committee!

465
00:51:54,505 --> 00:52:00,715
Students: Old Jiang! Old Jiang! Dachuang was captured by a gang of bad guys!

466
00:52:00,739 --> 00:52:01,729
Jiang Tao: Where?

467
00:52:01,753 --> 00:52:07,753
Students: At the newsstand, while selling journals, a guy with flattop led a gang, beating and robbing!

468
00:52:38,290 --> 00:52:42,290
Jiang Tao: You go back first. I’ll find Han Ling.

469
00:52:43,774 --> 00:52:44,854
Han Ling: Secretary Song?

470
00:52:49,350 --> 00:52:57,570
Song Secretary: No need! I’ve searched all Marxist-Leninist works, no quotes about the “Three Directives as the Key Link”!

471
00:52:57,594 --> 00:53:00,321
Han Ling: You just didn’t put in effort!

472
00:53:00,345 --> 00:53:09,438
I told you many times, hold a Standing Committee meeting to discuss this. Similar quotes will do!

473
00:53:10,427 --> 00:53:14,587
Jiang Tao is a worker; how much Marxism-Leninism does he understand?

474
00:53:19,375 --> 00:53:29,625
Hmm, see? This line is excellent! Powerful!

475
00:53:29,649 --> 00:53:32,039
Song Secretary: Secretary Han, your level is clear!

476
00:53:33,089 --> 00:53:36,029
Han Ling: Yes, you weren’t serious enough.

477
00:53:36,647 --> 00:53:40,977
Today is September 17th?

478
00:53:41,001 --> 00:53:42,031
Song Secretary: Yes.

479
00:53:48,278 --> 00:53:57,894
Han Ling: Hmph! Nine years ago, also today, Jiang Tao led people to rebel, right?

480
00:53:57,918 --> 00:54:02,458
Song Secretary: Yes, exactly, that kid led the trouble!

481
00:54:02,482 --> 00:54:04,977
Han Ling: Hmph hmph hmph hmph!

482
00:54:08,177 --> 00:54:17,617
See, this is ironclad proof! History will prove my innocence!

483
00:54:17,641 --> 00:54:19,811
Hmph hmph hmph hmph!

484
00:54:19,835 --> 00:54:30,305
Nine years, history played a big joke on us. Today, it ends!

485
00:54:44,288 --> 00:54:48,078
Han Ling: Ha ha ha ha, sit, sit, sit.

486
00:54:48,102 --> 00:55:00,602
Jiang Tao: Comrade Han Ling, an old worker, because he disagreed with your so-called rectification, was removed and criticized!

487
00:55:02,131 --> 00:55:10,711
This issue of the journal, for publishing a few anti-revisionist articles, was confiscated and sealed!

488
00:55:10,735 --> 00:55:20,035
Zhong Dachuang sold a few copies, and you arrested him. Why?

489
00:55:21,434 --> 00:55:25,554
What crime did they commit?

490
00:55:26,037 --> 00:55:37,637
Han Ling: What crime? Hmph. Today against this, tomorrow against that, now against the Provincial Committee, against the Central Committee!

491
00:55:38,446 --> 00:55:50,566
First telling university students to become peasants, then attacking professors, now opposing the “Three Directives as the Key Link"!

492
00:55:54,527 --> 00:55:59,727
Look, what did Zhong Dachuang write?

493
00:56:00,537 --> 00:56:09,667
He said some people, under the banner of achieving the Four Modernizations, oppose limiting bourgeois rights.

494
00:56:11,123 --> 00:56:13,973
Who does that refer to?

495
00:56:14,082 --> 00:56:18,032
Jiang Tao: Anyone treating bourgeois rights as their lifeline!

496
00:56:19,270 --> 00:56:22,160
Is it a crime to criticize bourgeois rights?

497
00:56:22,502 --> 00:56:27,732
Han Ling: Criticize bourgeois rights?!  Hmph, how revolutionary!

498
00:56:28,708 --> 00:56:42,428
But do you have enough material foundation? Can you launch satellites? Solve automation and mechanization? What will future society be like?

499
00:56:42,708 --> 00:56:51,253
The Cultural Revolution messed things up for nine years. Tens of millions of people in the province, what are they hoping for?

500
00:56:51,277 --> 00:57:02,612
They want more pork and vegetables in their baskets, bigger homes, better clothes.

501
00:57:02,636 --> 00:57:04,746
Jiang Tao: Your words give me inspiration!

502
00:57:16,339 --> 00:57:18,499
Here’s another famous line:

503
00:57:21,314 --> 00:57:24,554
“Revolutionary impulse alone is not enough.”

504
00:57:24,578 --> 00:57:28,188
Han Ling: Exactly, that’s empty talk, revolution only in fantasy!

505
00:57:28,212 --> 00:57:30,684
Jiang Tao: Listen further:

506
00:57:30,708 --> 00:57:36,876
“We also need a good dish of Goulash, books and decent housing,"

507
00:57:36,900 --> 00:57:43,330
"We should have more food, more good dishes, schools, homes, and ballet.” -Khrushchev

508
00:57:49,237 --> 00:57:57,764
Comrade Han Ling, you want to pin the blame for not modernizing or ignoring people’s lives on good comrades!

509
00:57:57,788 --> 00:58:02,471
But it’s precisely them who traversed thousands of miles along the Yellow River, finding solutions for sediment control!

510
00:58:02,495 --> 00:58:09,635
It’s them, day and night, working to produce machinery to manage the Yellow River!

511
00:58:09,659 --> 00:58:14,249
t’s them, carrying in their hearts tens of millions of people along the riverbanks!

512
00:58:14,273 --> 00:58:22,203
It’s them—good comrades removed, criticized, and suppressed by you!

513
00:58:22,227 --> 00:58:27,329
Han Ling: Comrade Jiang Tao, do you understand? We must achieve the Four Modernizations!

514
00:58:27,353 --> 00:58:29,591
Jiang Tao: We want modernization, yes,

515
00:58:31,286 --> 00:58:39,476
but we know if we don’t conduct class struggle, don’t implement proletarian dictatorship, don’t limit bourgeois rights,

516
00:58:39,500 --> 00:58:45,640
Party will turn revisionist, our country will change color!

517
00:58:46,925 --> 00:58:55,170
Even that so-called socialist country modernizes, but as their satellites go up, red flags come down!

518
00:58:55,334 --> 00:59:00,819
There, the revolutionaries live in prisons, wearing handcuffs and shackles!

519
00:59:00,843 --> 00:59:11,193
Han Ling: Don’t go too far. What we call “Three Directives as the Key Link combines politics and economics, and it has theoretical grounds.

520
00:59:13,645 --> 00:59:16,845
Listen to what Lenin said:

521
00:59:19,692 --> 00:59:29,792
“Viewing problems politically and economically has equal value.

522
00:59:29,816 --> 00:59:36,426
Both can be applied. Politics and economics must both be at the core.”

523
00:59:36,450 --> 00:59:44,670
Selected Works of Lenin, 1972 edition, Volume 4, page 441.

524
00:59:45,724 --> 00:59:49,464
The old masters weren’t wrong, were they?

525
00:59:49,488 --> 00:59:59,218
Comrades should read more Marxist books, or you’ll make big jokes of yourselves.

526
00:59:59,242 --> 01:00:02,352
Jiang Tao: Hahahahaha!

527
01:00:02,376 --> 01:00:04,726
Go on. Keep reading.

528
01:00:06,244 --> 01:00:12,684
Comrade Han Ling, what you just read was Lenin quoting Bukharin.

529
01:00:13,718 --> 01:00:18,520
Right after that comes Lenin’s ruthless criticism of Bukharin!

530
01:00:18,707 --> 01:00:33,725
Lenin said that claiming politics and economics have equal value
forgets the most basic knowledge of Marxism!

531
01:00:33,749 --> 01:00:43,729
Hahahaha! Comrade Han Ling, are you treating Bukharin as your revolutionary leader?

532
01:00:43,753 --> 01:00:46,453
Han Ling: Th-this was an accidental oversight!

533
01:00:46,477 --> 01:00:49,027
Jiang Tao: No, this was no accident at all.

534
01:00:49,051 --> 01:00:54,540
It shows that those who push restoration and regression instinctively follow opportunism!

535
01:00:54,564 --> 01:00:55,665
Han Ling: You’re outrageous!

536
01:00:57,223 --> 01:01:02,810
You know who proposed the “Three Directives as the Key Link!

537
01:01:02,834 --> 01:01:07,897
Keep this up, and you’d better think about the consequences.

538
01:01:10,385 --> 01:01:16,615
The Three Directives all come from Chairman Mao!

539
01:01:16,833 --> 01:01:20,033
Jiang Tao: Chairman Mao always emphasizes class struggle as the core.

540
01:01:21,515 --> 01:01:34,772
You selectively quote him to oppose proletarian dictatorship and the Party’s basic line.

541
01:01:34,858 --> 01:01:39,711
You use Chairman Mao’s banner to oppose Chairman Mao himself!

542
01:01:39,735 --> 01:01:41,095
Sister Zhao: Well said!

543
01:01:41,119 --> 01:01:42,159
Jiang Tao: Sister Zhao!

544
01:01:46,316 --> 01:01:51,716
Sister Zhao: We’ve already received hundreds of letters from workers, peasants, and soldiers.

545
01:01:54,574 --> 01:02:01,596
The hearts of the people and Party members reject your approach.

546
01:02:01,767 --> 01:02:12,615
Most Standing Committee members were furious that you seized the journal without discussion.

547
01:02:13,697 --> 01:02:19,359
They demand reporting this to Chairman Mao and the Central Committee.

548
01:02:19,592 --> 01:02:26,300
Also print 50,000 more copies to deliver Mao Zedong Thought to the masses!

549
01:02:26,324 --> 01:02:28,424
Jiang Tao: Sister Zhao, haha!

550
01:02:28,448 --> 01:02:32,728
Sister Zhao: Old Geng has been reinstated. Dachuang has returned to school.

551
01:02:32,752 --> 01:02:33,872
Jiang Tao: That's great!

552
01:02:37,051 --> 01:02:39,891
Han Ling: Contact Vice Premier Deng in Beijing!

553
01:02:50,449 --> 01:02:56,789
Lyrics: The Yellow River roars and rushes,

554
01:02:58,696 --> 01:03:04,886
I lift my head and face wind and rain.

555
01:03:05,766 --> 01:03:11,046
The revolutionary spark was sown by Chairman Mao…

556
01:03:14,572 --> 01:03:22,272
I brandish my spear across thirty thousand miles,

557
01:03:22,296 --> 01:03:28,816
Enduring bitter struggle, ranging freely through the vast fields of battle and labor.

558
01:03:30,629 --> 01:03:36,289
Riding the wind, treading the waves—

559
01:03:36,694 --> 01:03:51,893
Towards communism...

560
01:04:02,353 --> 01:04:04,413
Song Secretary: Xiaofang, why did you come back alone?

561
01:04:04,437 --> 01:04:07,617
Your father said a car would pick you up.

562
01:04:11,915 --> 01:04:13,535
Auntie: Xiaofang, you’re back?

563
01:04:13,559 --> 01:04:19,729
I heard your father plans to send you abroad to study.

564
01:04:19,753 --> 01:04:23,625
He says to learn real skills.

565
01:04:23,649 --> 01:04:28,427
Han Xiaofang: Where is my father?  Auntie: Fishing in the backyard.

566
01:04:28,451 --> 01:04:40,141
Han Ling: As an old comrade, I tried to save him, to stop him from sinking deeper.

567
01:04:53,000 --> 01:04:55,910
But things went against my wishes.

568
01:04:55,934 --> 01:05:01,864
Qiao Boren: Yes, Secretary Han has shown him utmost kindness.

569
01:05:03,815 --> 01:05:07,335
Wang Jian: Say it plainly. What exactly do you plan to do to Jiang Tao?

570
01:05:09,473 --> 01:05:16,113
Han Ling: Old Wang, look at this. My record of calls with the Central Committee.

571
01:05:17,868 --> 01:05:23,708
Comrade Deng criticized us for being indecisive and too soft.

572
01:05:25,342 --> 01:05:30,462
Wang Jian: Temporary demotion—how is that different from removal?

573
01:05:31,570 --> 01:05:33,610
Han Ling: You can interpret it yourself.

574
01:05:34,723 --> 01:05:46,673
Jiang Tao has attacked veteran cadres for years. You suffered from it too. You should expose him boldly.

575
01:05:47,840 --> 01:05:51,840
Wang Jian: Comrade Han Ling, isn’t this sowing discord?

576
01:05:53,518 --> 01:06:02,398
For seven or eight years, we worked and studied together. He never suppressed me, or you, Qiao Boren.

577
01:06:03,347 --> 01:06:10,534
He sincerely helped, encouraged, respected, and protected us.

578
01:06:10,597 --> 01:06:18,312
In him, I see the finest qualities of new cadres forged by the Cultural Revolution.

579
01:06:18,336 --> 01:06:24,394
I see a Communist with firm principles and fearless resistance to trends!

580
01:06:25,264 --> 01:06:30,344
Why make such a decision? This is persecution!

581
01:06:33,272 --> 01:06:44,702
Han Ling: Old Qiao, after removing Jiang Tao, abolish the open-door education sites immediately. Withdraw everyone from the dam project as well.

582
01:06:46,999 --> 01:06:56,014
So, Wang Jian is unreliable too. Remove him together.

583
01:06:56,038 --> 01:06:57,783
Qiao Boren: But he’s a veteran cadre.

584
01:06:57,807 --> 01:07:03,662
Han Ling: He is disobedient. Old and new alike—remove them step by step.

585
01:07:03,686 --> 01:07:05,711
Qiao Boren: Alright.

586
01:07:05,735 --> 01:07:11,635
Han Ling: Tonight, assist Secretary Song. Hold an expanded Party committee meeting at the university.

587
01:07:17,868 --> 01:07:32,588                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
Song Secretary: I will continue reading. Third: Comrade Zhang Hai of the Workers’ Propaganda Team is hereby removed from the post of Deputy Party Secretary of Yellow River University.

588
01:07:35,787 --> 01:07:44,706
Comrades Huang Di, Li Meng, and Li Haiquan of the Workers’ Propaganda Team are removed from their posts as members of the University Party Committee,

589
01:07:48,819 --> 01:07:52,749
and transferred back to their original work units.

590
01:08:12,905 --> 01:08:20,305
We hope you will return to your factories and make greater contributions to boosting the national economy.

591
01:08:21,663 --> 01:08:28,743
The education reform work previously under Comrade Zhang Hai will now be taken over by Xue Yaozong, Professor Xue.

592
01:08:33,364 --> 01:08:35,599
Wang Jian: At least explain the reasons.

593
01:08:35,623 --> 01:08:42,358
Qiao Boren: Isn’t it obvious? It’s to fully bring into play the role of senior professors.

594
01:08:42,382 --> 01:08:45,587
Song Secretary: Exactly right. Completely correct.

595
01:08:46,410 --> 01:08:55,495
All right, I will continue. Fourth:

596
01:08:55,519 --> 01:09:03,269
Comrade Jiang Tao has sabotaged the Party’s policy toward intellectuals, raised ultra-left slogans at will,

597
01:09:03,418 --> 01:09:10,968
put pressure on the Provincial Party Committee, opposed the implementation of the “Three Directives as the Key Link,”

598
01:09:10,992 --> 01:09:16,014
opposed comprehensive rectification, and undermined stability and unity.

599
01:09:16,038 --> 01:09:21,616
Therefore, the Provincial Party Committee has decided that Comrade Jiang Tao is to be sent down!

600
01:09:21,640 --> 01:09:27,880
Comrade Qiao Boren will serve as Acting Party Secretary of Yellow River University!

601
01:09:29,570 --> 01:09:32,490
Zhong Dachuang: This decision by the Provincial Party Committee is completely wrong!

602
01:09:32,514 --> 01:09:35,632
Old Geng: Hmph! Pure slander and frame-up!

603
01:09:35,656 --> 01:09:42,728
I protest this act of persecution and demand that the Provincial Party Committee revoke this decision!

604
01:09:54,818 --> 01:10:03,110
Jiang Tao: Comrades, whether it’s nominal assignment or comprehensive rectification,

605
01:10:03,134 --> 01:10:10,172
it all means one thing: everything we’ve done since the Cultural Revolution is being declared wrong!

606
01:10:10,196 --> 01:10:14,326
And everything they did before the Cultural Revolution is being declared right!

607
01:10:15,252 --> 01:10:19,324
Hmph! But they have forgotten one truth:

608
01:10:19,348 --> 01:10:29,616
restoration and regression are always short-lived, while new things are invincible!

609
01:10:41,282 --> 01:10:50,529
Our Party is a great, glorious, and correct Party. It has endured the test of ten line struggles,

610
01:10:50,553 --> 01:10:57,926
standing firm like the pillar in the middle reaches of the Yellow River, ready to meet a thousand—ten thousand—challenges!

611
01:11:06,320 --> 01:11:07,883
Song Secretary: Okey，okey...

612
01:11:07,908 --> 01:11:14,978
Song Secretary: No, no, They’re applauding Jiang Tao—this situation is getting out of control!

613
01:11:15,002 --> 01:11:18,865
Mm, yes, yes, that’s what I mean.

614
01:11:18,889 --> 01:11:25,169
As long as we convey the leaders’ instructions, the masses will come to their senses.

615
01:11:25,193 --> 01:11:30,093
All right, all right, Party Secretary Han, it’ll be done immediately.

616
01:11:32,452 --> 01:11:37,092
Old man, stop applauding—you’ve been fooled!

617
01:11:41,852 --> 01:11:48,952
Jiang Tao: Comrades, the next steps in the Party Committee’s work:

618
01:11:48,976 --> 01:11:55,411
First, we must continue to firmly grasp class struggle as the key link,

619
01:11:55,435 --> 01:11:59,740
seriously study the theory of the dictatorship of the proletariat throughout the college,

620
01:11:59,764 --> 01:12:05,164
and unswervingly run the school as an instrument of proletarian dictatorship.

621
01:12:06,439 --> 01:12:13,384
Second, we must uphold the direction of educational revolution and run schools with open doors.

622
01:12:13,602 --> 01:12:19,767
Of the original 97 open-door education sites, not a single one will be closed, the doors must be opened even wider!

623
01:12:22,016 --> 01:12:25,056
Those who agree with Comrade Jiang Tao’s proposal, raise your hands.

624
01:12:35,139 --> 01:12:41,809
Song Secretary: Comrades, comrades, comrades—don’t fall for his trick!

625
01:12:41,833 --> 01:12:45,883
Jiang Tao, stop being so stubbornly misguided!

626
01:12:45,907 --> 01:12:50,644
To be sent down is your chance to repent!

627
01:12:50,668 --> 01:12:54,381
He—he is inciting everyone to oppose the Central Committee!

628
01:12:55,269 --> 01:13:03,109
Comrades, comrades, let me be clear: the decision I read has backing!

629
01:13:04,352 --> 01:13:08,552
It was made in accordance with the spirit of Comrade Xiaoping’s directives!

630
01:13:21,692 --> 01:13:31,882
Jiang Tao: Comrades, no matter how fierce the winds and waves, the Yellow River will never flow backward!

631
01:13:34,019 --> 01:13:38,719
We must fight for the truth!

632
01:13:39,087 --> 01:13:40,487
Comrade Jiang Tao!

633
01:15:14,667 --> 01:15:20,627
Jiang Tao: Why does Qiao Boren dare to drag out again things that were thoroughly criticized and condemned seventeen years ago?

634
01:15:31,678 --> 01:15:56,952
Why does Han Ling openly oppose the Cultural Revolution and overturn its verdicts? Can Deng Xiaoping represent the Party Central Committee?

635
01:15:56,976 --> 01:16:04,989
Chairman Mao said: beware of revisionism, especially beware of revisionism emerging in the Central Committee!

636
01:16:24,304 --> 01:16:33,069
Xiao Mei: Dad, people say you made a huge mistake.

637
01:16:33,093 --> 01:16:36,353
They say you’re an ambitious schemer who wants to be a big official!

638
01:16:41,065 --> 01:16:45,180
Jiang Tao: Dad doesn’t like tears, huh?

639
01:16:45,771 --> 01:16:48,796
Xiao Mei: Dad, let’s go back to the factory!

640
01:16:48,820 --> 01:16:53,340
Grandpa Geng and the others all like you. Mom says she’ll come get you and take you back to the factory!

641
01:17:01,072 --> 01:17:03,242
Jiang Tao: Xiao Mei, go to sleep.

642
01:17:03,266 --> 01:17:03,975
Xiao Mei: Mm.

643
01:17:14,189 --> 01:17:19,629
Jiang Tao: Yumei, this is the first time you’ve come to pick me up, isn’t it?

644
01:17:24,085 --> 01:17:31,255
The War of Liberation, the Great Movement to Resist America and Assist Korea—you sent me to the battlefield.

645
01:17:33,324 --> 01:17:43,604
Collectivization, harnessing the Yellow River, the Anti-Rightist Movement, the Cultural Revolution—you sent me to fight every time.

646
01:17:44,574 --> 01:17:49,144
But you’ve never come to bring me back from the battlefield.

647
01:17:49,168 --> 01:17:56,838
Yumei: Old Jiang, going back to the factory is still making revolution. We workers will fight them together.

648
01:17:59,838 --> 01:18:06,008
Jiang Tao: The working class ascended to the superstructure because Chairman Mao sent us there.

649
01:18:08,185 --> 01:18:13,905
If Chairman Mao asked why we returned to the factory, what should we say?

650
01:18:18,039 --> 01:18:26,585
Yumei: You love the Party and love Chairman Mao.
I know you’ve carried out the revolution through wind and rain.

651
01:18:28,633 --> 01:18:43,973
But now people say you oppose the Provincial Party Committee, oppose the Party, oppose the Central Committee…

652
01:18:47,880 --> 01:18:49,320
Jiang Tao: Do you believe that?

653
01:18:53,276 --> 01:19:07,556
Half a century ago, Chairman Mao led our Party through repeated fierce struggles against erroneous lines.

654
01:19:09,060 --> 01:19:15,460
Chen Duxiu, Liu Shaoqi, Lin Biao—all waved the banner of the Central Committee!

655
01:19:17,978 --> 01:19:24,510
Can today’s Deng Xiaoping represent the Party Central Committee?  Yumei: Of course not!

656
01:19:24,534 --> 01:19:31,197
Jiang Tao: But they still hold a great deal of power, from the center to the localities.

657
01:19:31,221 --> 01:19:34,786
That’s where the complexity of the struggle lies!

658
01:19:35,713 --> 01:19:43,033
We must unite with the broad masses and confront the revisionist line head-on!

659
01:20:15,233 --> 01:20:16,403
Old Geng: Jiang Tao!

660
01:20:16,427 --> 01:20:20,287
Jiang Tao: Comrade Old Geng, why are you here?

661
01:20:20,311 --> 01:20:23,371
Old Geng: The comrades at the factory asked me to come see you!

662
01:20:23,395 --> 01:20:26,632
Yumei: Oh—Uncle Geng!

663
01:20:26,656 --> 01:20:29,388
Old Geng: Yumei, why are there people keeping watch downstairs?

664
01:20:29,412 --> 01:20:32,263
Old Geng: Probably “guards” sent by Han Ling for me!

665
01:20:32,287 --> 01:20:34,097
Old Geng: Damn scoundrels!

666
01:20:36,902 --> 01:20:46,609
Last night they already announced your nominal assignment decision at the construction site—the workers didn’t give them the time of day!

667
01:20:46,789 --> 01:20:57,692
The comrades at the factory discussed it and sent me here overnight to tell you to hold firm. The entire working class stands with you!

668
01:20:57,716 --> 01:20:59,216
Jiang Tao: Comrade Old Geng!

669
01:21:06,060 --> 01:21:15,760
Old Geng: Before I left, the comrades asked me to bring you this.

670
01:21:40,040 --> 01:21:42,440
Jiang Tao: Comrades, follow me!

671
01:21:51,411 --> 01:21:55,771
Comrade Old Geng, Comrade Old Geng, quick!

672
01:22:18,664 --> 01:22:25,814
Comrade Old Geng, this red flag is stained with the blood of our working class!

673
01:22:27,441 --> 01:22:32,281
We must forever occupy the battlefield of education!

674
01:22:34,302 --> 01:22:38,742
We must launch uninterrupted attacks against the bourgeoisie!

675
01:22:49,795 --> 01:22:53,765
Old Liu, old Jiang doing this—I’m really worried for him.

676
01:22:53,789 --> 01:22:57,369
What are you afraid of? The sky won’t fall!

677
01:22:57,393 --> 01:23:03,103
Won’t fall? Just wait and see. Jiang Tao is so arrogant—he won’t end well!

678
01:23:05,322 --> 01:23:09,742
Who are you trying to scare? You work so hard for the capitalist roaders—what benefits do you get?

679
01:23:11,266 --> 01:23:15,266
Old Jiang! Old Jiang!

680
01:23:16,415 --> 01:23:21,065
Director Qiao has gone to Liujiadu to dismantle the site. Even the motorboats transporting equipment have been blocked!

681
01:23:21,089 --> 01:23:24,559
Zhong Dachuang: How can that work? Without pontoon cranes, how can we transport anything up?

682
01:23:24,583 --> 01:23:26,703
Jiang Tao: Let’s go—let’s take a look!

683
01:23:26,727 --> 01:23:30,047
Auntie Tian: Auntie will ferry you over on a leather raft.

684
01:23:30,955 --> 01:23:34,495
Qiao Boren: Comrades, dismantle faster—pack faster!

685
01:23:34,519 --> 01:23:37,769
Get all the personnel and tents onto the first truck!

686
01:23:37,793 --> 01:23:45,733
Hurry up! Hurry up! We don't have much time!

687
01:23:45,757 --> 01:23:47,699
Professor Xue: Yes—hurry up!

688
01:23:48,595 --> 01:23:54,033
Qiao Boren: Even if you don’t want to leave, you have to. These are orders from above!

689
01:23:54,057 --> 01:23:55,267
Professor Xue: Exactly!

690
01:23:55,291 --> 01:23:59,101
Xiao Hong, Shen Niu—stop dawdling!

691
01:23:59,125 --> 01:24:00,655
Qiao Boren: Load it up!

692
01:24:15,800 --> 01:24:17,200
Faster! Faster! Faster! Move it!

693
01:24:18,842 --> 01:24:19,962
Faster!

694
01:24:23,768 --> 01:24:25,898
Qiao Boren: Comrade Old Geng, goodbye!

695
01:24:25,922 --> 01:24:31,229
Sorry to have caused you so much trouble. Please give us more valuable opinions!

696
01:24:31,253 --> 01:24:36,626
Old Geng: Old Qiao means for me to say a few words. Fine—I’ll say a few words!

697
01:24:37,600 --> 01:24:43,190
Qiao Boren: Keep it brief. The wind’s picking up—don’t let the students get soaked!

698
01:24:43,214 --> 01:24:46,206
Old Geng: The students we send out won’t be ruined by a little rain!

699
01:24:46,230 --> 01:24:53,678
Students, those of you studying water conservancy should also learn this:

700
01:24:53,702 --> 01:25:04,962
learn to tell the wind’s direction—is it blowing from the southeast or the northwest? Do you go with the wind and waves first, or against the wind and waves first?

701
01:25:04,986 --> 01:25:06,826
Qiao Boren: All right, that’s enough. That’s enough!

702
01:25:08,608 --> 01:25:14,913
Old Geng: Pah! Students, let me continue what I was saying just now.

703
01:25:14,937 --> 01:25:20,090
No matter how many bends the Yellow River makes, it always flows into the sea!

704
01:25:20,114 --> 01:25:24,549
I believe that after weathering this storm, you will come back!

705
01:25:25,195 --> 01:25:33,236
The Crowd: Comrade Old Geng!

706
01:25:33,260 --> 01:25:38,990
Qiao Boren: What are you doing? What are you doing? First truck—drive off!

707
01:25:39,014 --> 01:25:40,124
Jiang Tao: Don’t move!

708
01:25:40,573 --> 01:25:43,880
 Old Zheng, you finally came. And old Jiang. 

709
01:25:44,252 --> 01:25:46,542
Jiang Tao: Old Qiao, you want to shut down this site?

710
01:25:46,567 --> 01:25:47,538
Yes.


711
01:25:47,562 --> 01:25:49,972
The Party Committee has decided—no site is to be shut down!

712
01:25:50,339 --> 01:25:52,879
Qiao Boren: Comrade Jiang Tao!

713
01:25:52,903 --> 01:25:56,803
You should understand that right now I am presiding over the Party Committee’s work!

714
01:25:56,827 --> 01:26:01,147
Jiang Tao: Then I ask you to follow the Party Committee’s resolution and lead everyone along Chairman Mao’s revolutionary line!

715
01:26:01,171 --> 01:26:02,291
Qiao Boren: Jiang Tao, you—

716
01:26:04,008 --> 01:26:07,238
Professor Xue, Professor Wen—we’re leaving!

717
01:26:07,262 --> 01:26:10,499
Professor Wen: We’re not going the same road anymore!

718
01:26:10,523 --> 01:26:13,156
Qiao Boren: Old Xue, let’s go!

719
01:26:13,180 --> 01:26:14,505
Hmph!

720
01:26:15,406 --> 01:26:16,846
Jiang Tao: Comrades!

721
01:26:16,870 --> 01:26:18,295
Comrades!

722
01:26:18,319 --> 01:26:22,654
In order to ensure that the first phase of the project is completed within three days,

723
01:26:22,678 --> 01:26:27,473
all revolutionary teachers and students here are to concentrate at the dam construction site and fight a war of annihilation,

724
01:26:27,497 --> 01:26:32,967
to realize Chairman Mao’s great call to get the Yellow River under control!

725
01:26:32,991 --> 01:26:35,756
The motorboats are blocked—so what!

726
01:26:35,780 --> 01:26:39,830
We’ll pull and haul by hand first, advancing straight into the wind and waves!

727
01:28:18,243 --> 01:28:26,843
Song Secretary: Secretary Han, Secretary Han—Jiang Tao shows no sign of giving in at all.

728
01:28:26,867 --> 01:28:30,467
Wang Jian is the same—still confronting us head-on!

729
01:28:31,705 --> 01:28:34,145
Han Ling: Mm. All right.

730
01:28:38,159 --> 01:28:40,749
Song Secretary: The construction site is plastered with big-character posters,

731
01:28:41,153 --> 01:28:48,263
calling you capitalist-roaders isn’t enough anymore, they said “capitalist-roaders still on the road”!

732
01:28:48,287 --> 01:28:53,889
Han Ling: How is it that they’ve dragged out that whole Cultural Revolution set again?

733
01:28:53,913 --> 01:29:00,232
Qiao Boren: With Jiang Tao stirring things up like this, and with Wang Jian backing the open-door education sites, not a single one has been shut down.

734
01:29:00,256 --> 01:29:05,219
Song Secretary: What’s even more serious is that the big-character posters say "we must beware of revisionism emerging in the Central Committee."

735
01:29:05,243 --> 01:29:14,063
Han Ling: Hmph! These posters aren’t just aimed at me—they’re directly attacking Vice Premier Deng!

736
01:29:17,339 --> 01:29:21,499
No wonder Vice Premier Deng criticized me for being soft!

737
01:29:23,621 --> 01:29:25,781
Remove Wang Jian!

738
01:29:28,867 --> 01:29:38,207
As for Jiang Tao—I’ll arrange a “suitable place” for him!

739
01:29:52,308 --> 01:29:53,619
Dolma?

740
01:29:53,643 --> 01:29:56,732
Dolma: Auntie! Jiang Tao has been taken away!

741
01:29:56,756 --> 01:29:58,606
Auntie Tian: They’ve shown their malicious intent!

742
01:29:58,630 --> 01:30:02,260
The Crowd: Let’s go! Hurry! Hurry! Hurry!

743
01:30:22,615 --> 01:30:23,895
Voices: Jiang Tao!

744
01:30:24,528 --> 01:30:26,528
Voices: Jiang Tao!

745
01:30:30,945 --> 01:30:32,632
Return-to-the-Village Corps

746
01:30:34,352 --> 01:30:35,814
Jiang Tao: Return-to-the-Village Corps!

747
01:30:38,334 --> 01:30:39,934
Auntie Tian: Return-to-the-Village Corps!

748
01:30:44,456 --> 01:30:53,666
Thirty years ago, right under this old locust tree, Return-to-the-Village Corps also arrested people!

749
01:30:56,090 --> 01:31:06,780
Back then, Han Ling was the regional Party secretary here. He said a new stage of “peace and democracy” had arrived.

750
01:31:07,788 --> 01:31:14,308
When he came to our area, he ordered the disbandment of village militia units.

751
01:31:16,852 --> 01:31:29,782
One night—one night—Return-to-the-Village Corps slipped into our village.

752
01:31:33,619 --> 01:31:44,109
They burned and looted, and Pan Ling was seized by them too.

753
01:31:44,133 --> 01:31:50,533
Back then, Jiang Tao was the head of our village’s Children’s Corps.

754
01:32:07,608 --> 01:32:11,569
Ah ah!

755
01:32:20,140 --> 01:32:22,140
Ah ah!

756
01:32:40,901 --> 01:32:43,581
Return-to-the-Village Corps: Where is he?

757
01:32:43,605 --> 01:32:45,565
Over there! Chase him, you bastard!

758
01:32:49,114 --> 01:32:51,754
Jiang Tao: Quick! Run that way!

759
01:32:58,552 --> 01:33:00,912
Return-to-the-Village Corps: Get him! Where did that little brat run off to?

760
01:33:02,430 --> 01:33:07,720
Finish him! Over there! Over there—quick!

761
01:33:14,061 --> 01:33:18,146
FXXK!


762
01:33:38,220 --> 01:33:40,320
Auntie Tian: Jiang Tao!

763
01:33:44,391 --> 01:33:52,471
Blood — you’re hurt!

764
01:33:52,495 --> 01:33:57,775
Auntie Tian: In these thirty years, people have walked very different roads.

765
01:33:59,731 --> 01:34:10,791
Han Ling, whom Jiang Tao once saved, entered the city after Liberation and became a high official, and his heart drifted farther and farther away from the people.

766
01:34:12,751 --> 01:34:25,171
He was involved in dismantling cooperatives, in the big push for household responsibility system, and in suppressing the Cultural Revolution!

767
01:34:26,865 --> 01:34:44,135
Who would have thought—Han Ling, who himself was once arrested by the Return-to-the-Village Corps, becomes one today and seize Jiang Tao!

768
01:34:44,228 --> 01:34:47,268
Zhong Dachuang: We must settle accounts with the capitalist-roaders!

769
01:34:47,292 --> 01:34:59,452
Auntie Tian: Child, don’t cry! Fight them like Jiang Tao and Sister Zhao did!

770
01:34:59,476 --> 01:35:09,881
Sister Zhao: Comrade Han Ling, ever since you were reinstated, everything you’ve done has stood in opposition to Chairman Mao’s revolutionary line!

771
01:35:09,905 --> 01:35:18,830
Now you’ve even privately detained Comrade Jiang Tao—this violates Party discipline and state law!

772
01:35:18,854 --> 01:35:28,039
Han Ling: Comrade Zhao Xin, you should know that Jiang Tao’s anti-Party, anti-Central stance is the essence of the problem!

773
01:35:28,063 --> 01:35:34,443
Sister Zhao: Then put your so-called “essence” on the Provincial Party Committee agenda, and make it public to the people of the entire province!

774
01:35:35,531 --> 01:35:45,401
Han Ling: Hmph! Jiang Tao dares to do this because he’s not isolated—someone has been backing him all along!

775
01:35:45,821 --> 01:35:49,646
Sister Zhao: Hmph-hmph, that’s right! I’m backing him!

776
01:35:49,670 --> 01:35:57,640
Digging out the backstage supporters—there’s nothing frightening about that. We crossed snow-capped mountains and grasslands following Chairman Mao.

777
01:35:57,664 --> 01:36:03,634
If anyone insists on pushing an erroneous line—it won’t work!

778
01:36:10,295 --> 01:36:15,772
Narration: Seven guards were replaced in succession; even the cook came under Jiang Tao’s influence.

779
01:36:15,796 --> 01:36:23,729
Song Secretary: Secretary Han, we’ve interrogated him many times—he’s still that die-hard type. Nothing will come out of him.

780
01:36:26,449 --> 01:36:33,789
Han Ling: Even if there are no results, we still have to try. Director Zhao has already filed several complaints to the Center, and the masses keep coming to make trouble.

781
01:36:33,813 --> 01:36:34,593
Song Secretary: Then?

782
01:36:34,617 --> 01:36:39,606
Han Ling: It’s fine. The initiative is still in our hands.

783
01:36:39,630 --> 01:36:44,480
As long as he changes his stance, Old Lady Zhao’s appeals will be completely nullified!

784
01:36:49,904 --> 01:36:53,794
Song Secretary: Heh heh heh heh heh—Comrade Jiang Tao!

785
01:36:53,818 --> 01:37:00,455
Outrageous! Outrageous! Just look at how they’re handling this!

786
01:37:00,479 --> 01:37:09,282
Party Secretary Han spoke to them several times, telling them not to put this on you—heh heh heh heh!

787
01:37:09,306 --> 01:37:14,336
Jiang Tao: Just speak plainly! What new trick are you trying to pull today?

788
01:37:14,360 --> 01:37:20,000
Song Secretary: No, no, no—today Party Secretary Han is personally here to see you.

789
01:37:20,895 --> 01:37:22,695
Han Ling: Ah, Old Jiang!

790
01:37:24,321 --> 01:37:33,371
Ha ha ha ha—how’s your health lately? Still good?

791
01:37:34,944 --> 01:37:41,104
Jiang Tao: Very good! Your penal methods can't hurt me at all!

792
01:37:45,591 --> 01:37:48,591
Han Ling: Hmph-hmph! Still as stubborn as ever!

793
01:37:50,229 --> 01:37:58,169
Jiang Tao: Time to pin down a charge! Is my crime “anti-restoration,” or “opposing revisionism and preventing revisionism”?

794
01:37:58,309 --> 01:38:02,199
Han Ling: Ah—let’s not talk about that. Let’s not talk about that!

795
01:38:02,223 --> 01:38:20,165
Old Jiang, I know you. Didn’t we once have a bond of shared life-and-death, fighting side by side?

796
01:38:20,189 --> 01:38:24,477
Jiang Tao: Back then we walked the same road, but our hearts were never aligned.

797
01:38:25,715 --> 01:38:35,795
Isn’t meeting here today a clearer statement of our class relationship than sitting on the Provincial Committee’s sofas?

798
01:38:35,819 --> 01:38:40,189
Han Ling: Don’t look at it that way, Old Jiang.

799
01:38:43,493 --> 01:38:53,233
These past eight or nine years, I’ve realized one thing: old grudges should be resolved, not prolonged.

800
01:38:56,202 --> 01:39:01,242
Jiang Tao: These past eight or nine years, I’ve also grasped one truth:

801
01:39:01,642 --> 01:39:13,022
The struggle between the revolutionary camp and the capitalist-roaders is a life-and-death class struggle!

802
01:39:17,724 --> 01:39:30,704
Han Ling: I advise you to face reality. With Vice Premier Deng presiding over the Central work, the overall situation is settled!

803
01:39:30,813 --> 01:39:38,093
If you keep writing inspections like this, you’ll never have a future!

804
01:39:38,133 --> 01:39:41,521
(Further discussion on the fact that the capitalist roaders are still on the capitalist path)

805
01:39:42,806 --> 01:39:46,326
Jiang Tao: You’re determined not to follow Chairman Mao anymore!

806
01:39:46,606 --> 01:39:50,806
Anyone who wants to bring down our Party will find it’s not that easy!

807
01:39:53,731 --> 01:40:05,021
Han Ling: All right, all right, Old Jiang—don’t be so short-sighted!

808
01:40:05,130 --> 01:40:17,300
I’m already over sixty years old. As long as you follow us, won’t it be you who takes over this Provincial Committee leadership in the future?

809
01:40:17,324 --> 01:40:18,944
Jiang Tao: Despicable and shameless!

810
01:40:25,178 --> 01:40:28,183
Get out of here!

811
01:40:28,207 --> 01:40:31,937
Han Ling: Jiang Tao! Don’t try to play the hero!

812
01:40:31,961 --> 01:40:42,236
Have you ever thought about this—when you silently disappear from this world, as someone who "oppose Party," how painful would it be?

813
01:40:42,260 --> 01:40:46,245
You should know—you’re sitting in a proletarian prison cell!

814
01:40:47,774 --> 01:40:53,289
Jiang Tao: You capitalist-roaders can turn the instruments of proletarian dictatorship into tools of bourgeois dictatorship!

815
01:40:53,460 --> 01:41:01,245
As a Communist Party member, to sacrifice everything for the cause of communism fills me with supreme honor and happiness!

816
01:41:02,628 --> 01:41:10,955
I firmly believe Marxism-Leninism will triumph! The communist ideal will certainly be realized!

817
01:41:11,142 --> 01:41:13,105
Han Ling: Put that thing on him!

818
01:41:16,548 --> 01:41:21,748
Jiang Tao: Han Ling, the revolutionary people will punish you!

819
01:42:09,526 --> 01:42:22,486
(Writing a letter) Respected Chairman Mao: In our country of proletarian dictatorship, who can throw Communists into prison?

820
01:42:23,708 --> 01:42:38,008
The Kuomintang cannot do it. Landlords and capitalists cannot do it. Yet the Party’s capitalist-roaders in power have done it!

821
01:42:42,115 --> 01:42:52,012
You profoundly pointed out that when revisionism comes to power, it means the bourgeoisie has come to power.

822
01:42:52,036 --> 01:43:03,469
I firmly believe that our great leader Chairman Mao will surely lead us in a massive counter-attack against revisionism…

823
01:45:09,730 --> 01:45:13,170
Xiao Mei: Mom, will we be able to see Dad soon?

824
01:45:16,026 --> 01:45:16,626
Yumei: Yes.

825
01:45:17,905 --> 01:45:24,265
Sister Zhao: Yumei, don’t be sad. Isn’t everything better now?

826
01:45:24,289 --> 01:45:28,104
Our great leader Chairman Mao has spoken for us!

827
01:45:28,128 --> 01:45:33,800
Yumei: Yes… after hearing Chairman Mao’s words, I couldn't even sleep last night.

828
01:45:33,824 --> 01:45:41,867
Sister Zhao: It’s been several months—so hard. I went to see him several times and they wouldn’t allow it.

829
01:45:41,891 --> 01:45:49,049
Later I went to the Provincial Committee to find you—who would have thought they’d take you down too.

830
01:45:49,073 --> 01:45:52,343
So vicious!

831
01:45:57,519 --> 01:46:01,029
Xiao Mei: Mom, does dad work here now?

832
01:46:01,053 --> 01:46:04,823
Mom, tell me—tell me!

833
01:46:16,911 --> 01:46:21,032
Xiao Mei: Dad! We’re here to take you home!

834
01:46:23,095 --> 01:46:24,095
Dad!

835
01:46:37,636 --> 01:46:38,836
Jiang Tao: Sister Zhao!

836
01:46:42,945 --> 01:46:44,305
Sister Zhao: Comrade Jiang Tao!

837
01:46:48,819 --> 01:46:49,819
Jiang Tao.

838
01:47:07,261 --> 01:47:14,761
Auntie Tian: Child, you’ve suffered so much!

839
01:47:16,590 --> 01:47:17,470
Jiang Tao: Auntie.

840
01:47:19,295 --> 01:47:23,095
Auntie Tian: The capitalist-roaders’ hearts are truly poisonous!

841
01:47:35,252 --> 01:47:37,420
Yumei: Old Jiang.

842
01:47:37,444 --> 01:47:38,243
Jiang Tao: Yumei.

843
01:47:43,330 --> 01:47:46,390
Yumei: Now Chairman Mao has spoken for us.

844
01:47:46,414 --> 01:47:48,154
Old Jiang—look!

845
01:47:55,092 --> 01:47:56,377
Chairman Mao!

846
01:47:57,148 --> 01:47:59,988
Background: Long live Chairman Mao!

847
01:48:01,584 --> 01:48:02,984
Long live!

848
01:48:05,252 --> 01:48:06,892
Jiang Tao: Long live Chairman Mao!

849
01:48:21,217 --> 01:48:25,857
Jiang Tao: Heh-heh—now the situation is excellent! The masses are rising in a mighty surge!

850
01:48:25,881 --> 01:48:30,001
Sister Zhao: Yes! That means we leading cadres must stand at the front of the movement!

851
01:48:30,025 --> 01:48:31,945
Comrade Old Jiang—here are the materials for you.

852
01:48:33,313 --> 01:48:38,893
Jiang Tao: I was just looking for you. Everything else is good—I changed two spots.

853
01:48:38,924 --> 01:48:43,696
Tell them to seriously study the theory of proletarian dictatorship and firmly grasp the overall direction of criticizing Deng.

854
01:48:43,720 --> 01:48:44,860
Sure!

855
01:48:44,884 --> 01:48:48,313
Yao Mingli: Xiao Fang, forget about studying abroad.

856
01:48:48,337 --> 01:48:50,300
As long as your father doesn’t fall, everything is manageable!

857
01:48:50,324 --> 01:48:51,213
Jiang Tao: Xiaofang!

858
01:48:51,237 --> 01:48:54,287
Yao Mingli: Jiang Tao—goodbye.

859
01:48:55,188 --> 01:48:57,248
Xiaofang, I’ll wait for you tonight!

860
01:48:57,272 --> 01:48:58,217
Han Xiaofang: All right!

861
01:48:58,878 --> 01:49:01,245
Jiang Tao: Why did you come back?

862
01:49:01,269 --> 01:49:03,101
Han Xiaofang: Something came up.

863
01:49:03,125 --> 01:49:05,273
Jiang Tao: Do you really know him?

864
01:49:05,297 --> 01:49:08,137
Han Xiaofang: Yao Mingli? What about him?

865
01:49:09,205 --> 01:49:14,925
He’s from a worker background, studied in the Soviet Union, has real skills, and treats me quite well.

866
01:49:16,660 --> 01:49:21,460
Jiang Tao: Xiaofang—you must stay alert around him.

867
01:49:22,643 --> 01:49:33,233
In real class struggle, if someone refuses to align themselves with workers and peasants, counter-revolutionaries may very well align themselves with him.

868
01:49:34,237 --> 01:49:39,977
Sister Zhao: Good—send it out immediately. We shall promote production through criticizing Deng.

869
01:49:40,001 --> 01:49:40,621
Good!

870
01:49:42,923 --> 01:49:45,003
Director Zhao, phone call from Beijing!

871
01:49:46,298 --> 01:49:49,928
Old Geng: Old Jiang! You’re here—I’ve been looking everywhere!

872
01:49:49,952 --> 01:49:58,442
All workers of the Yellow River Hydraulics Machinery Factory unanimously propose that the province-wide criticism assemblies be held right on the Yellow River dam,

873
01:49:58,466 --> 01:50:02,296
and that we use the iron facts of flood-release and sediment discharge to criticize Deng Xiaoping!

874
01:50:02,320 --> 01:50:07,770
Jiang Tao: Great! We’re thinking alike! Heh-heh—this way we both report success and criticize Deng!

875
01:50:07,794 --> 01:50:11,664
Old Geng: Right—release the water first, then make speeches!

876
01:50:11,688 --> 01:50:13,848
Both: Hahahahahaha!

877
01:50:13,872 --> 01:50:16,762
Jiang Tao: Good! Let the Yellow River cheer for us!

878
01:50:16,786 --> 01:50:18,786
OK, ok.

879
01:50:25,478 --> 01:50:28,598
Sister Zhao: Chairman Mao and the Central Committee have repeatedly emphasized

880
01:50:28,622 --> 01:50:34,262
that leading cadres must stand on the front line of struggle, taking the lead in exposing and criticizing.

881
01:50:35,173 --> 01:50:44,583
The Central Committee’s care for cadres is truly meticulous—but unfortunately Han Ling won’t listen to a single word.

882
01:50:44,607 --> 01:50:49,397
Yesterday I talked to him again—same as always.

883
01:50:49,479 --> 01:50:54,411
Once Chairman Mao’s instruction was published, he collapsed and stopped working.

884
01:50:54,435 --> 01:50:58,643
Jiang Tao: I think he goes all-out for revisionism, and falls “ill” whenever socialism is involved!

885
01:50:58,667 --> 01:51:03,107
Hmph—says he’s sick, but he’s busier than ever lately.

886
01:51:04,780 --> 01:51:09,720
Secretary Song has been really active recently.

887
01:51:09,744 --> 01:51:14,199
Sister Zhao: Their abnormal activities are not isolated—

888
01:51:14,223 --> 01:51:19,398
they’re closely tied to new developments in class struggle.

889
01:51:19,422 --> 01:51:22,472
Look—this is the latest enemy situation report.

890
01:51:25,080 --> 01:51:27,880
Class struggle is becoming more and more complex.

891
01:51:39,093 --> 01:51:44,753
Secretary Song: Party Secretary Han, Qiao Boren and Professor Xue both said they had matters to attend to and couldn’t come.

892
01:51:44,777 --> 01:51:47,757
They’re becoming harder and harder to invite.

893
01:51:50,371 --> 01:51:57,011
Han Ling: Hmph—short-sighted rats! Do they think we’re finished?

894
01:51:58,890 --> 01:52:01,651
Is Comrade Xiaoping still working or not?

895
01:52:03,924 --> 01:52:07,674
Things are already stirring up in front of Tiananmen in Beijing—

896
01:52:07,698 --> 01:52:11,735
and here, the smell of gunpowder is just as strong!

897
01:52:11,759 --> 01:52:18,453
Song Secretary: Yes, Party Secretary Han. According to this enemy-situation report,

898
01:52:18,477 --> 01:52:21,600
Yao Mingli has been frequently contacting Han Xiaofang.

899
01:52:22,217 --> 01:52:26,396
Cheers！Cheers！


900
01:52:30,013 --> 01:52:32,423
Crowd: Hey—the Chairman’s back!

901
01:52:32,447 --> 01:52:44,307
Yao Mingli: Let me introduce everyone—this is the son of Provincial Party Secretary Han, Han Xiaofang.

902
01:52:44,331 --> 01:52:50,191
Chatter

903
01:52:50,230 --> 01:52:59,540
Biaozi: You still remember me, Biaozi, right? Ahahahaha! We used to vacation together!

904
01:53:00,178 --> 01:53:02,178
Ha ha ha.

905
01:53:04,576 --> 01:53:16,886
Then the Cultural Revolution came, investigations started—my old man suddenly became a traitor. Now it’s your old man’s turn!

906
01:53:16,910 --> 01:53:18,910
Ha ha ha.

907
01:53:18,934 --> 01:53:25,331
Old Ke: Uh, I say, Han Xiaofang, we invite you to join our Committee for Saving the Four Modernizations.

908
01:53:25,355 --> 01:53:27,708
Let’s take them on together!

909
01:53:31,839 --> 01:53:38,675
Right now Secretary Han’s stance at the provincial level is extremely favorable to us.

910
01:53:38,699 --> 01:53:49,269
Yao Mingli: Old Ke, once our cause succeeds, the “rightist” label on you can be exchanged for a ministerial crown!

911
01:53:49,619 --> 01:53:54,917
Old Ke: Hahahaha! I’ve been waiting for this day!

912
01:53:54,942 --> 01:53:56,563
Once it’s done, we hang Jiang Tao first!

913
01:53:56,923 --> 01:53:58,923
Yes! Hang him!

914
01:54:02,703 --> 01:54:06,720
What—scared?

915
01:54:07,013 --> 01:54:12,026
Han Xiaofang: Didn’t you say you called me here to discuss realizing the Four Modernizations?

916
01:54:12,050 --> 01:54:13,365
Nerd!

917
01:54:13,389 --> 01:54:18,046
Hahahahahahahahahaha!

918
01:54:18,070 --> 01:54:21,013
The Four Modernizations—haha!

919
01:54:21,065 --> 01:54:22,655
First comes power!

920
01:54:24,255 --> 01:54:27,747
They have began their move in front of Tiananmen!

921
01:54:27,771 --> 01:54:32,539
We must also launch a big push under the banner of Deng!

922
01:54:32,702 --> 01:54:41,712
In real class struggle, if a person refuses to align himself with workers and peasants, counter-revolutionaries may very well align themselves with him.

923
01:54:43,682 --> 01:54:52,142
Stop! No one is allowed to go home tonight! We’ll discuss everything tomorrow morning!

924
01:55:33,466 --> 01:55:42,518
Jiang Tao: Comrades, to ensure the success of the sediment discharge, we will conduct one more check before the mass meeting convenes.

925
01:55:42,954 --> 01:55:45,132
Each group, report your readiness.

926
01:55:45,156 --> 01:55:46,886
Crane ready!

927
01:55:46,910 --> 01:55:48,530
Observation instruments ready!

928
01:55:48,554 --> 01:55:50,504
Hydrological measurements ready!

929
01:55:50,528 --> 01:55:53,166
Jiang Tao: Good! Ready...! 

930
01:55:53,190 --> 01:55:56,225
Yao Mingli: Don’t open the gates!

931
01:55:56,249 --> 01:55:57,889
Don’t open the gates!

932
01:55:57,913 --> 01:56:01,933
Fellow villagers! Fellow villagers!

933
01:56:01,957 --> 01:56:05,014
If we open the tunnel’s bottom outlet,

934
01:56:05,038 --> 01:56:08,168
this hillside will collapse!

935
01:56:08,441 --> 01:56:12,908
The dam will fail!

936
01:56:13,437 --> 01:56:18,148
Several counties downstream on the Yellow River will be destroyed!

937
01:56:18,288 --> 01:56:23,418
All flooded by the Yellow River!

938
01:56:24,505 --> 01:56:28,642
We will all be finished!

939
01:56:28,666 --> 01:56:33,399
Chatter

940
01:56:33,423 --> 01:56:35,920
Zhong Dachuang: Comrades!

941
01:56:35,944 --> 01:56:38,157
This is complete rumor-mongering!

942
01:56:38,181 --> 01:56:42,281
We have tested this hundreds of times, the dam will absolutely not collapse!

943
01:56:42,305 --> 01:56:44,475
Chatter

944
01:56:47,359 --> 01:56:55,354
Yao Mingli: Fellow villagers, I am from the provincial committee! I cannot speak against my conscience!

945
01:56:55,378 --> 01:56:58,368
Chatter

946
01:56:58,392 --> 01:57:02,917
Open the tunnel bottom outlet and the dam will collapse!

947
01:57:02,941 --> 01:57:04,571
Chatter

948
01:57:04,595 --> 01:57:11,917
Party Secretary Han, out of concern for everyone’s lives and property, imported dredging ships from abroad!

949
01:57:11,941 --> 01:57:14,129
But Jiang Tao refuses to use them!

950
01:57:14,153 --> 01:57:23,203
Old Geng: Yao Mingli! Those dredging ships were bought by the provincial capitalist-roader Han Ling, following Deng Xiaoping’s instructions,

951
01:57:23,227 --> 01:57:28,837
bought a few wacky foreign ships with huge amount of oil, and they are completely useless!

952
01:57:29,837 --> 01:57:37,857
Yao Mingli, you know this very well. You have ulterior motives to bring up those dredging ships today!

953
01:57:37,881 --> 01:57:46,331
Yao Mingli: Don’t listen to him! Party Secretary Han wants everyone to live a good life! Jiang Tao’s purpose is to strike at veteran cadres!

954
01:57:46,355 --> 01:57:48,985
[Chatter]

955
01:57:49,009 --> 01:57:56,632
Yao Mingli: Comrades! Today’s meeting is chaired by the Committee for Saving the Four Modernizations!

956
01:57:57,434 --> 01:58:01,568
Old Geng: Yao Mingli, get down! What are you doing?

957
01:58:01,592 --> 01:58:03,403
Zhong Dachuang: What is Committee for Saving the Four Modernizations?

958
01:58:03,427 --> 01:58:07,657
Chatter

959
01:58:07,681 --> 01:58:15,310
Secretary Song: I never expected trouble to break out on the dam. From the looks of it, the masses still support you very strongly!

960
01:58:24,311 --> 01:58:28,399
Han Ling: Hehehe… Jiang Tao, let’s see how you’re going to clean this up!

961
01:58:28,423 --> 01:58:35,892
Jiang Tao: Yes, yes—that’s right, Director Zhao. They’ve already openly raised the banner of the Committee for Saving the Four Modernizations.

962
01:58:35,916 --> 01:58:41,339
Sister Zhao: Mm! Yes. We’ll take action according to the provincial committee’s predetermined plan!

963
01:58:41,379 --> 01:58:42,149
Jiang Tao: Good!

964
01:58:44,801 --> 01:58:48,631
Zhong Dachuang: Old Jiang, mobilize the militia immediately and arrest those bastards!

965
01:58:48,655 --> 01:58:51,935
Jiang Tao: They must be arrested—but not immediately.

966
01:58:51,959 --> 01:58:54,014
Zhong Dachuang: Then what do we do now?

967
01:58:54,038 --> 01:59:01,213
Jiang Tao: Some of the masses have been misled. Two types of contradictions are mixed together. At moments like this, the more we must stay calm.

968
01:59:04,195 --> 01:59:11,705
Think about it—why do they dare to so recklessly sabotage the criticism meeting? Why do they bring up Han Ling's name?

969
01:59:11,729 --> 01:59:13,999
Zhong Dachuang: You mean the capitalist-roaders are backing them?

970
01:59:14,784 --> 01:59:18,284
Jiang Tao: Exactly. Their heart is inside the Party!

971
01:59:18,308 --> 01:59:23,890
Only by first exposing the capitalist-roaders can we educate the misled masses,

972
01:59:23,914 --> 01:59:28,712
then isolate the small handful of counterrevolutionaries and subject them to ruthless suppression!

973
01:59:28,736 --> 01:59:30,736
Zhong Dachuang: Good!

974
01:59:30,760 --> 01:59:34,550
Jiang Tao: Wait. Go notify the militia command—have all units assemble and stand by. I’m going to the dam immediately!

975
01:59:34,574 --> 01:59:36,094
Zhong Dachuang: Yes!

976
01:59:37,157 --> 01:59:38,460
Counterrevolutionaries: Where’s Jiang Tao?!

977
01:59:38,484 --> 01:59:40,045
Come out so we can beat Jiang Tao to death!

978
01:59:40,069 --> 01:59:42,419
Jiang Tao! Jiang Tao! Come out!

979
01:59:42,443 --> 01:59:44,333
Jiang Tao: What are you doing?!

980
01:59:56,734 --> 01:59:58,734
Who sent you here?!

981
01:59:59,388 --> 02:00:02,428
I am the representative of the poor and lower-middle peasants along both banks of the Yellow River!

982
02:00:02,452 --> 02:00:03,572
Crowd: You’re a counterrevolutionary!

983
02:00:08,188 --> 02:00:16,515
Jiang Tao: Comrades! Comrades! I now announce on behalf of the provincial committee, they are a counterrevolutionary organization!

984
02:00:16,539 --> 02:00:19,122
What they are doing today is absolutely not an isolated incident!

985
02:00:19,146 --> 02:00:24,361
In recent days, in front of Tiananmen in Beijing, a gang of counterrevolutionary rioters has been doing exactly the same thing!

986
02:00:24,385 --> 02:00:28,455
Zhong Dachuang: Whoever dares to make trouble where Chairman Mao lives, we overthrow them!

987
02:00:28,479 --> 02:00:32,114
Dolma: Whoever dares to make trouble at Tiananmen, we emancipated serfs will never allow it!

988
02:00:32,138 --> 02:00:34,450
Crowd: Resolutely suppress counterrevolutionaries!

989
02:00:34,474 --> 02:00:36,832
Defend the Central Committee!

990
02:00:36,856 --> 02:00:38,756
Defend Chairman Mao!

991
02:00:38,780 --> 02:00:46,340
Han Xiaofang: Old Jiang, I was wrong!

992
02:01:02,528 --> 02:01:05,820
Firmly support Secretary Han！

993
02:01:07,820 --> 02:01:09,448
Secretary Han！Secretary Han！

994
02:01:09,472 --> 02:01:13,732
Jiang Tao is suppressing revolutionary masses!

995
02:01:13,756 --> 02:01:17,366
Han Ling: Don’t arrest people—let them go!

996
02:01:20,252 --> 02:01:28,662
Firmly support Secretary Han! Firmly support Secretary Han!

997
02:01:34,097 --> 02:01:44,156
Han Ling: Comrades! I arrived one step too late! The emergence of such a situation—I bear responsibility!

998
02:01:46,210 --> 02:01:57,102
Today’s meeting was approved by the provincial committee. Therefore, any interference with this meeting is wrong!

999
02:01:58,580 --> 02:02:04,328
Counterrevolutionary A: Damn it, why are you singing this tune too?
B: You don’t know shit—listen carefully!

1000
02:02:04,352 --> 02:02:13,582
Han Ling: Different opinions—and even erroneous opinions—can emerge among the masses. Free debate should be allowed!

1001
02:02:13,606 --> 02:02:18,268
Jiang Tao: You are speaking on behalf of the enemy! We absolutely do not grant counterrevolutionaries freedom of speech!

1002
02:02:18,292 --> 02:02:27,100
Han Ling: Jiang Tao, a new cadre must learn how to correctly treat mass movements. I have lessons in this regard.

1003
02:02:27,124 --> 02:02:36,584
Jiang Tao: Last year, during the rightist reversal wind, you carried out brutal suppression of revolutionary masses. Did you speak then about “correct treatment”?

1004
02:02:36,608 --> 02:02:47,538
Today a small handful of counterrevolutionaries want to seize power from the Party, and you call it a mass movement! Which class are you protecting, exactly?!

1005
02:03:18,687 --> 02:03:23,697
Han Ling: I am still the provincial Party secretary! Without my order, no militia may be mobilized!

1006
02:03:23,721 --> 02:03:29,411
Jiang Tao: Once counterrevolutionary disturbances appear on the dam, immediately deploy militia for suppression, this was decided by the provincial standing committee!

1007
02:03:29,435 --> 02:03:35,705
Han Ling: On what basis did you make this decision?! This violates Party discipline and state law!

1008
02:03:35,729 --> 02:03:45,036
Jiang Tao: On what basis? It’s written in Marx’s books, Lenin’s books, and Chairman Mao’s books: the dictatorship of the proletariat must be exercised over the bourgeoisie!

1009
02:03:45,060 --> 02:03:53,123
This is our Party discipline and state law! Without this protective shield, proletarians would die! This is the lesson of history!

1010
02:03:53,147 --> 02:03:57,307
Yumei: Old Jiang, look at these reactionary leaflets—they’re vicious!

1011
02:03:57,331 --> 02:03:59,191
This is their Open Letter to the People of the Whole Province!

1012
02:04:02,811 --> 02:04:12,081
Jiang Tao: Han Ling, they write reactionary leaflets, viciously attack Chairman Mao, split the Central Committee, and openly support Deng, they are not "revolutionary mass"!

1013
02:04:13,869 --> 02:04:16,309
All militia units—move out immediately!

1014
02:04:28,673 --> 02:04:32,202
Sister Zhao: Comrade Jiang Tao must suppress them resolutely!

1015
02:04:32,227 --> 02:04:42,335
These mobs here are extremely rampant, we must resolutely implement the dictatorship of the proletariat!

1016
02:05:03,332 --> 02:05:04,692
Militia: Take them away! Move!

1017
02:05:04,716 --> 02:05:09,916
Crowd: Long live the dictatorship of the proletariat!

1018
02:05:10,591 --> 02:05:12,551
Long live the Communist Party of China!

1019
02:05:21,475 --> 02:05:23,955
Long live Chairman Mao!

1020
02:05:23,979 --> 02:05:25,969
Long live Chairman Mao!

1021
02:05:26,663 --> 02:05:39,391
Jiang Tao: Comrades! A small handful of counterrevolutionaries want to manufacture a Hungarian-style counterrevolutionary incident on our soil!

1022
02:05:40,598 --> 02:05:45,614
They can only bring about their own destruction under the iron fist of the dictatorship of the proletariat!

1023
02:05:47,780 --> 02:05:52,220
Today’s facts teach us: we must deepen the criticism of Deng,

1024
02:05:53,413 --> 02:05:56,423
and carry the struggle against the rightist reversal wind through to the end!

1025
02:05:56,447 --> 02:06:02,184
Otherwise, counterrevolutionaries in society, relying on capitalist-roaders in the Party,

1026
02:06:02,208 --> 02:06:06,751
can openly use violence to seize power from the Communist Party!

1027
02:06:08,542 --> 02:06:12,302
Recently, our great leader Chairman Mao pointed out:

1028
02:06:13,206 --> 02:06:17,746
in carrying out the socialist revolution, if you don’t know where the bourgeoisie is,

1029
02:06:17,770 --> 02:06:25,957
it is inside the Communist Party, the capitalist-roaders in power within the Party, the capitalist-roaders are still taking the road!

1030
02:06:25,981 --> 02:06:28,124
Song Secretary: Jiang Tao is targeting you.

1031
02:06:28,148 --> 02:06:31,388
Han Ling: Jiang Tao, I will report you to the Central Committee!

1032
02:06:31,412 --> 02:06:34,809
Jiang Tao: The “Central Committee” you speak of is nothing but Deng Xiaoping!

1033
02:06:34,833 --> 02:06:42,506
But what decides China’s fate, are the hundreds of millions of heroic people tempered by the Great Proletarian Cultural Revolution!

1034
02:06:45,000 --> 02:06:47,200
Long live Chairman Mao!

1035
02:07:00,871 --> 02:07:06,756
Sister Zhao: Comrade Jiang Tao, I bring you extremely great news!

1036
02:07:07,036 --> 02:07:12,271
The Central Committee and Chairman Mao have issued two resolutions of major historical significance!

1037
02:07:12,295 --> 02:07:14,495
Jiang Tao: Excellent! Announce them immediately!

1038
02:07:16,309 --> 02:07:19,129
Sister Zhao: Everyone, quiet down!

1039
02:07:19,153 --> 02:07:21,933
Now announcing the Central resolutions!

1040
02:07:22,360 --> 02:07:27,560
Comrades, I report to you extraordinarily great news!

1041
02:07:28,690 --> 02:07:35,810
The Central Committee and Chairman Mao have issued two resolutions of major historical significance:

1042
02:07:40,052 --> 02:07:45,642
First: The Resolution of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China appointing Comrade Hua Guofeng

1043
02:07:45,666 --> 02:07:51,183
as First Vice Chairman of the CPC Central Committee

1044
02:07:51,207 --> 02:07:55,870
and Premier of the State Council of the People’s Republic of China!

1045
02:07:56,890 --> 02:08:00,290
Crowd: Long live Chairman Mao!

1046
02:08:01,917 --> 02:08:06,654
Long live Premier Hua Guofeng!

1047
02:08:06,678 --> 02:08:15,911
Second: The Resolution of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China to remove Deng Xiaoping from all Party and state positions!

1048
02:08:16,219 --> 02:08:22,169
Crowd: Long live Chairman Mao!

1049
02:08:22,193 --> 02:08:24,553
Long live the Communist Party of China!

1050
02:08:24,577 --> 02:08:26,127
Long live Chairman Mao!

1051
02:08:26,151 --> 02:08:27,888
Long live the Communist Party of China!

1052
02:08:27,912 --> 02:08:30,915
Resolutely support the two Central Committee resolutions!

1053
02:08:30,939 --> 02:08:34,387
Deeply criticize Deng Xiaoping’s counterrevolutionary revisionist line!

1054
02:08:34,411 --> 02:08:37,951
Deeply criticize Deng Xiaoping’s counterrevolutionary revisionist line!

1055
02:08:39,469 --> 02:08:52,469
Resolutely support the two Central Committee resolutions!

1056
02:08:56,358 --> 02:08:57,358
Jiang Tao: Comrades!

1057
02:08:59,029 --> 02:09:01,929
Our heroic revolutionary people—

1058
02:09:01,976 --> 02:09:05,486
like the endlessly surging furious waves of the Yellow River—

1059
02:09:05,510 --> 02:09:09,650
will sweep all the filth and silt that block history’s advance...

1060
02:09:09,674 --> 02:09:11,764
...into the vast ocean!

1061
02:09:11,788 --> 02:09:16,365
Let us, generation after generation, follow closely our great leader Chairman Mao,

1062
02:09:17,183 --> 02:09:26,816
 and launch one hundred times, one thousand times, ten thousand times great counterattacks against the bourgeoisie! Open the gates!

